C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-long-will-take-cancel-student-debt-higher-education-act-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattempting%20relief%20using%20a%20different%20law%3A%20the%20Higher%20Education%20Act%20of%201965%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20opposed%20to%20the%20HEROES%20Act%2C%20though%2C%20the%20Higher%20Education%20Act%20requires%20the%20administration%20go%20through%20the%20negotiated%20rulemaking%20process%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-timeline-for-biden-new-student-debt-relief-2023-7%5C%22%3Ewhich%20could%20take%20at%20least%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20it%20includes%20holding%20public%20hearings%20and%20a%20series%20of%20negotiations%20to%20craft%20the%20final%20debt-relief%20plan.%20Last%20month%2C%20the%20department%20held%20its%20public%20hearing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ed.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fbiden-harris-administration-seeks-nominations-non-federal-negotiators-continue-rulemaking-process-student-debt-relief%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20is%20seeking%20nominations%20for%20non-federal%20negotiators%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20negotiating%20sessions%20beginning%20in%20October.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20against%20the%20Biden-Harris%20Administration's%20student%20debt%20relief%20plan%2C%20we%20did%20not%20waste%20a%20moment%20opening%20up%20a%20new%20pathway%20to%20debt%20relief%2C%26quot%3B%20Education%20Secretary%20Miguel%20Cardona%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ed.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fbiden-harris-administration-seeks-nominations-non-federal-negotiators-continue-rulemaking-process-student-debt-relief%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we%20pursue%20debt%20relief%20through%20this%20process%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20steps%20is%20bringing%20together%20diverse%20perspectives%20to%20help%20us%20craft%20the%20strongest%20possible%20regulations%20for%20borrowers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Student%20Loan%20Relief%20committee%20will%20include%20students%2C%20borrowers%2C%20state%20officials%2C%20civil%20rights%20advocates%2C%20representatives%20from%20colleges%20and%20universities%2C%20and%20other%20stakeholders%20so%20we%20can%20make%20sure%20all%20voices%20are%20heard%20and%20the%20needs%20of%20borrowers%20are%20fully%20considered.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20press%20release%2C%20negotiations%20will%20be%20held%20virtually%20on%20October%2010-11%2C%20November%206-7%2C%20and%20December%2011-12%2C%20and%20they%20will%20be%20open%20to%20the%20public%20with%20opportunities%20for%20public%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%2014%20spots%20the%20department%20is%20seeking%20nominations%20for%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFour%20spots%20for%20current%20students%20and%20student-loan%20borrowers%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFour%20spots%20for%20different%20types%20of%20institutions%2C%20including%20Historically%20Black%20Colleges%20and%20Universities%20and%20minority-serving%20institutions%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETwo%20spots%20for%20state%20officials%20and%20attorneys%20general%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETwo%20spots%20for%20civil%20rights%20organizations%20and%20legal%20assistance%20organizations%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20spot%20for%20a%20military%20service%20member%20or%20veteran%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnd%20one%20spot%20for%20someone%20from%20the%20Federal%20Family%20Education%20Loan%20program.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENominations%20can%20be%20emailed%20to%20negregnominations%40ed.gov%20by%20September%2014%2C%20and%20they%20must%20include%20which%20group%20the%20nominee%20falls%20into%2C%20their%20resume%20and%20experience%2C%20and%20contact%20information.%20Following%20the%20negotiations%2C%20the%20department%20will%20publish%20the%20proposed%20student-debt%20relief%20for%20public%20comment%20and%20%26quot%3Bproduce%20final%20regulations%20next%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20press%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20latest%20step%20comes%20just%20days%20before%20the%20student-loan%20payment%20pause%20ends%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-interest-resume-federal-student-loan-debt-payment-pause-2023-7%5C%22%3Einterest%20is%20beginning%20to%20accrue%20again%20on%20Friday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20bills%20becoming%20due%20in%20October.%20Since%20borrowers%20will%20not%20be%20entering%20repayment%20with%20broad%20relief%2C%20the%20department%20also%20announced%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdo-i-have-to-resume-student-loan-payments-debt-relief-2023-7%5C%22%3E12-month%20%26quot%3Bon-ramp%26quot%3B%20period%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20which%20missed%20payments%20will%20not%20be%20reported%20to%20credit%20agencies%2C%20but%20interest%20will%20still%20accrue%20during%20that%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Biden%20recently%20announced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-income-driven-repayment-adjustment-debt-relief-biden-2023-8%5C%22%3E%2439%20billion%20in%20debt%20relief%20for%20over%20800%2C000%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20a%20one-time%20account%20adjustment%20for%20borrowers%20on%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans%2C%20and%20the%20department%20will%20evaluate%20borrowers'%20accounts%20every%20two%20months%20to%20determine%20others%20that%20have%20met%20the%20qualifying%2020%20or%2025%20years%20of%20payments%20on%20those%20plans%20for%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20while%20the%20department%20is%20moving%20forward%20with%20the%20broad%20debt%20relief%20process%2C%20its%20future%20is%20uncertain%20due%20to%20conservative%20opposition%20%E2%80%94%20and%20potential%20legal%20challenges%20that%20could%20once%20again%20halt%20relie