tps%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2305.17493.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bmodel%20collapse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20In%20turn%2C%20the%20researchers%20claim%20that%20generative%20AI%20tools%20may%20respond%20to%20user%20queries%20with%20lower-quality%20outputs%2C%20as%20their%20models%20become%20more%20widely%20trained%20on%20%26quot%3Bsynthetic%20data%26quot%3B%20instead%20of%20the%20human-made%20content%20that%20make%20their%20responses%20unique.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20AI%20researchers%20have%20coined%20their%20own%20terms%20to%20describe%20the%20training%20method.%20In%20a%20paper%20released%20in%20July%2C%20researchers%20from%20Stanford%20and%20Rice%20universities%20called%20this%20phenomenon%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2307.01850.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BModel%20Autography%20Disorder%2C%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20which%20the%20%26quot%3Bself-consuming%26quot%3B%20loop%20of%20AI%20training%20itself%20on%20content%20generated%20by%20other%20AI%20could%20result%20in%20generative%20AI%20tools%20%26quot%3Bdoomed%26quot%3B%20to%20have%20their%20%26quot%3Bquality%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdiversity%26quot%3B%20of%20images%20and%20text%20generated%20falter.%20Jathan%20Sadowski%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Emerging%20Technologies%20Research%20Lab%20in%20Australia%20who%20researches%20AI%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fjathansadowski%2Fstatus%2F1625245803211272194%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalled%20this%20phenomenon%20%26quot%3BHabsburg%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20arguing%20that%20AI%20systems%20heavily%20trained%20on%20outputs%20of%20other%20generative%20AI%20tools%20can%20create%20%26quot%3Binbred%20mutant%26quot%3B%20responses%20that%20contain%20%26quot%3Bexaggerated%2C%20grotesque%20features.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20specific%20effects%20of%20these%20phenomena%20are%20still%20unclear%2C%20some%20tech%20experts%20believe%20that%20%26quot%3Bmodel%20collapse%26quot%3B%20and%20AI%20inbreeding%20could%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20pinpoint%20the%20original%20source%20of%20information%20an%20AI-model%20is%20trained%20on.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20providers%20of%20accurate%20information%20such%20as%20the%20media%20may%20decide%20to%20limit%20the%20content%20they%20post%20online%20%E2%80%94%20even%20putting%20it%20behind%20paywalls%20%E2%80%94%20to%20prevent%20their%20content%20from%20being%20used%20to%20train%20AI%2C%20which%20could%20create%20a%20%26quot%3Bdark%20ages%20of%20public%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.raywang.org%2Fblog%2F2023-08%2Fmondays-musings-will-generative-ai-drive-humanity-dark-ages-knowledge%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20essay%20written%20by%20Ray%20Wang%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20tech%20research%20firm%20Constellation%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20tech%20experts%20are%20less%20worried%20about%20the%20growth%20of%20AI-generated%20content%20on%20the%20internet.%20Saurabh%20Baji%2C%20the%20senior%20VP%20of%20engineering%20at%20AI-firm%20Cohere%2C%20told%20Axios%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2023%2F08%2F28%2Fai-content-flood-model-collapse%3Futm_source%3Dnewsletter%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3Dnewsletter_axioswhatsnext%26stream%3Dscience%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuman%20guidance%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20%26quot%3Bstill%20critical%20to%20the%20success%20and%20quality%26quot%3B%20of%20its%20AI-generated%20models%2C%20and%20others%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20the%20rise%20of%20AI-generated%20content%20will%20only%20make%20human-crafted%20content%20more%20valuable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20new%20terms%20come%20as%20AI-generated%20content%20has%20flooded%20the%20internet%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20launched%20ChatGPT%20last%20November%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20of%20August%2028%2C%20NewsGuard%2C%20a%20company%20that%20rates%20the%20reliability%20of%20news%20websites%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsguardtech.com%2Fspecial-reports%2Fai-tracking-center%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eidentified%20452%20%26quot%3Bunreliable%20AI-generated%20news%20outlets%20with%20little%20to%20no%20human%20oversight%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20contain%20stories%20filled%20with%20errors.%20AI-generated%20sites%20with%20generic%20names%20like%20iBusiness%20Day%2C%20Ireland%20Top%20News%2C%20and%20Daily%20Time%20Update%20may%20appeal%20to%20consumers%20as%20accurate%20sources%20of%20information%2C%20which%20would%20bolster%20the%20spread%20of%20misinformation%2C%20according%20to%20NewsGuard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20AI-generated%20websites%20that%20have%20produced%20articles%20filled%20with%20inaccuracies.%20In%20January%2C%20tech%20publication%20CNET%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcnet-slashes-10-staff-says-cuts-unrelated-ai-generated-content-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%2077%20articles%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%20an%20%26quot%3Binternally%20designed%20AI%20engine%26quot%3B%20and%20had%20to%20issue%20significant%20corrections%20after%20learning%20that%20its%20articles%20were%20riddled%20with%20basic%20math%20errors.%20Months%20later%2C%20Gizmodo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgizmodo-goof-proves-ai-errors-basic-facts-star-wars-chronology-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecriticized%20company%20executives%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20media%20outlet%20published%20AI-written%20articles%20with%20factual%20inaccuracies.%20Most%20recently%2C%20Microsoft%20removed%20a%20string%20of%20articles%20from%20its%20travel%20blog%2C%20one%20of%20which%20was%20found%20to%20be%20an%20AI-generated%20article%20recommending%20visitors%20in%20Ottawa%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-