gets360.com%2Fmobiles%2Fnews%2Fiphone-15-series-date-confirmed-apple-launch-event-wonderlust-september-12-4340740%2Famp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20Goes%20Underground%20In%20Aksai%20Chin%20-%20What%20It%20Means%20For%20Indian%20Forces%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESixty%20kilometres%20east%20of%20the%20Depsang%20Plains%20in%20Northern%20Ladakh%2C%20Chinese%20forces%20have%20begun%20carving%20tunnels%20and%20shafts%20into%20a%20hillside%20along%20a%20narrow%20river%20valley%20to%20construct%20multiple%20reinforced%20shelters%20and%20bunkers%20for%20soldiers%20and%20weaponry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20site%20identified%20in%20this%20report%20lies%20in%20Aksai%20Chin%2C%20East%20of%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%2C%20in%20territory%20held%20by%20China%20and%20historically%20claimed%20by%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternational%20geo-intelligence%20experts%2C%20who%20have%20analysed%20the%20images%20sourced%20by%20NDTV%20from%20Maxar%20for%20over%20a%20week%2C%20have%20identified%20the%20presence%20of%20at%20least%2011%20portals%20or%20shafts%20bored%20into%20the%20rockface%20on%20both%20banks%20of%20the%20river%20valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%229dttjcdo%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F9dttjcdo_maxar-satellite-tunnel_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESatellite%20images%20indicate%20the%20existence%20of%20at%20least%2011%20shafts%20bored%20into%20the%20rockface.%20Several%20earth-moving%20machines%20visible%C2%A0(High%20res%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F%253ca%2520href%3D%2522https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Ft21g4lp8_maxar-satellite-aksai-chin-hd-1_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%2522%253ehere%253c%2Fa%253e%5C%22%3EClick%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20high-resolution%20pic)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20images%20show%20massive%20construction%20activity%20over%20the%20last%20few%20months%20and%20are%20a%20likely%20attempt%20to%20protect%20heavy%20weaponry%20and%20soldiers%20from%20Indian%20airstrikes%20and%20extended-range%20artillery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20exclusive%20interview%20with%20NDTV%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20Foreign%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20rubbished%20China's%20latest%20move%20to%20claim%20Indian%20territory%20as%20its%20own%20by%20including%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Aksai%20Chin%20in%20its%20new%20%26quot%3Bstandard%20map%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20has%20put%20out%20maps%20with%20territories%20(that%20are)%20not%20theirs.%20(It%20is%20an)%20old%20habit.%20Just%20by%20putting%20out%20maps%20with%20parts%20of%20India...%20this%20doesn't%20change%20anything.%20Our%20government%20is%20very%20clear%20about%20what%20our%20territory%20is.%20Making%20absurd%20claims%20does%20not%20make%20other%20people's%20territories%20yours%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20see%20China's%20activities%20in%20Aksai%20Chin%20as%20an%20act%20of%20desperation%20to%20offset%20India's%20advantage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20establishing%20underground%20facilities%20and%20developing%20subterranean%20infrastructure%20in%20such%20proximity%20to%20the%20border%2C%20Chinese%20strategists%20seem%20to%20be%20aiming%20to%20counterbalance%20the%20current%20advantage%20held%20by%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20in%20Aksai%20Chin%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Damien%20Symon%2C%20a%20leading%20satellite%20imagery%20expert%20with%20The%20Intel%20Lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22mb0nvh9%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fmb0nvh9_maxar-satellite-tunnel-2_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClose%20up%20of%20two%20tunnel%20entrances%C2%A0(High%20res%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F%253ca%2520href%3D%2522https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F8qco269_maxar-satellite-aksai-chin-hd-2_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%2522%253ehere%253c%2Fa%253e%5C%22%3EClick%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20high-resolution%20pic)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESameer%20Joshi%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20NewSpace%20Research%20%26amp%3B%20Technologies%2C%20a%20leading%20Indian%20drone%20start-up%2C%20agrees.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20years%20since%20the%20Galwan%20clash%2C%20the%20Indian%20Army%20has%20effectively%20scaled%20up%20its%20offensive%20fire%20vectors%2C%20especially%20long-range%20tube%20and%20rocket%20artillery.%26quot%3B%20The%20Chinese%20decision%20to%20carve%20into%20hillsides%2C%20Mr%20Joshi%20says%2C%20is%20directly%20linked%20to%20greater%20Indian%20offensive%20capability.%20%26quot%3BThe%20massive%20construction%20activity%2C%20including%20hardened%20shelters%2C%20bunkers%2C%20tunnels%2C%20and%20the%20widening%20of%20roads%20is%20being%20done%20to%20mitigate%20this%20clear%20and%20present%20danger%20which%20the%20Indian%20Army%20has%20imposed%20on%20the%20Chinese%20deployment%20doctrine%20in%20Tibet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20operates%20a%20host%20of%20frontline%20airbases%20ranged%20against%20China%20across%20the%20Ladakh%20front.%20While%20Srinagar%20and%20Avantipura%20have%20traditionally%20been%20frontline%20IAF%20fighter%20bases%2C%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20is%20also%20looking%20to%20extend%20the%20runway%20at%20the%20Air%20Landing%20Ground%20in%20Nyoma%2C%20which%20is%20located%20at%20an%20altitude%20of%2013%2C700%20feet%20near%20the%20Pangong%20Lake.%20Extending%20the%20runway%20at%20Nyoma%20would%20enable%20the%20IAF%20to%20host%20fighter%20aircraft%20less%20than%2050%20kilometres%20from%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22mkl6ngug%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fmkl6ngug_maxar-satellite-aksai-chin_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20activities%20in%20Aksai%20Chin%20are%20being%20seen%20by%20experts%20as%20acts%20of%20desperation%20to%20offset%20India's%20advantage%C2%A0(High%20res%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F%253ca%2520href%3D%2522https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Ffuevj48o_maxar-satellite-aksai-chin-6_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%2522%253ehere%253c%2Fa%253e%5C%22%3EClick%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20high-resolution%20pic)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20clear%20that%20China%20is%20hardening%20its%20military%20presence%20in%20Ladakh%20against%20possible%20artillery%20and%20airstrikes%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20full-scale%20military%20escalation%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sim%20Tack%2C%20the%20Chief%20Military%20Analyst%20at%20Force%20Analysis%2C%20which%20provides%20data%20and%20analysis%20on%20armed%20conflicts%20and%20defence%20policy.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20see%20what%20are%20likely%20reinforced%20command%20positions%20and%20underground%20equipment%20storage%20facilities.%20Such%20facilities%20greatly%20enhance%20the%20Chinese%20ability%20to%20continue%20operations%20and%20limit%20attrition%20if%20an%20armed%20conflict%20were%20to%20break%20out%20in%20Ladakh.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMultiple%20berms%20and%20revetments%20of%20the%20site%20in%20December%202021%20indicate%20that%20the%20location%20had%20been%20identified%20as%20a%20key%20staging%20point%20during%20the%20height%20of%20the%20India-China%20faceoff%20in%20Ladakh%20when%20Chinese%20forces%20had%20made%20multiple%20incursions%20into%20the%20Indian%20territory%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control.%20This%20same%20area%20has%20now%20been%20completely%20transformed%20with%20massive%2C%20ongoing%20construction%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22q9j7heg%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fq9j7heg_maxar-satellite-tunnel-3_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMultiple%20reinforced%20personnel%20bunkers%20have%20been%20carved%20into%20the%20hillside%20with%20entry%20and%20exit%20areas%20designed%20to%20dissipate%20the%20impact%20of%20pressure%20from%20bombardment%C2%A0(High%20res%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F%253ca%2520href%3D%2522https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F9drfk24_maxar-satellite-aksai-chin-hd-3_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%2522%253ehere%253c%2Fa%253e%5C%22%3EClick%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20high-resolution%20pic)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20images%2C%20from%20August%2018%2C%20indicate%20the%20presence%20of%20four%20reinforced%20personnel%20bunkers%20constructed%20along%20the%20valley%20face%2C%20along%20with%20three%20tunnel%20areas%2C%20with%20two%20and%20five%20portals%20or%20tunnels%20at%20each%20site%2C%20carved%20onto%20the%20hillside.%20Heavy%20earth-moving%20machinery%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20multiple%20locations.%20A%20primary%20road%2C%20which%20cuts%20across%20the%20valley%2C%20has%20been%20substantially%20widened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20images%20also%20show%20that%20the%20earth%20has%20been%20raised%20around%20the%20personnel%20bunkers%20to%20provide%20additional%20protection%20from%20direct%20attacks.%20Entry%20and%20exit%20areas%20have%20a%20distinctive%20fork%20design%20meant%20to%20dissipate%20the%20impact%20of%20pressure%20from%20bombardment%20and%20feature%20raised%20earth%20berms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina's%20creation%20of%20permanent%20bunkers%20and%20other%20fortifications%20in%20Aksai%20Chin%20meshes%20with%20its%20broader%20intransigence%2C%20with%20no%20sign%20that%20it%20is%20willing%20to%20climb%20down%20to%20some%20extent%20to%20end%20the%20extended%20military%20standoff%20with%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Brahma%20Chellaney%2C%20among%20India's%20most%20authoritative%20watchers%20of%20China.%20%26quot%3BThe%20construction%20activity%20in%20Aksai%20Chin%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20mirrors%20China's%20creation%20of%20new%20permanent%20military%20structures%20in%20other%20border%20areas%20extending%20from%20eastern%20Ladakh%20and%20the%20middle%20sector%20to%20the%20Arunachal-Tibet%20frontier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%222kq0b8e%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F2kq0b8e_maxar-satellite-before-after_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESatellite%20imagery%20from%20December%202021%20of%20the%20river%20valley%20in%20Aksai%20Chin%20shows%20minimal%20construction%20activity.%20The%20site%20has%20been%20completely%20transformed%20by%20August%202023%C2%A0(High%20res%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F%253ca%2520href%3D%2522https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fvmtlbj7o_maxar-satellite-aksai-chin-hd-4_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%2522%253ehere%253c%2Fa%253e%5C%22%3EClick%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20high-resolution%20pic)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20India%20and%20China%20have%20attempted%20to%20de-escalate%20the%20crisis%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20by%20establishing%20no-patrol%20zones%2C%20the%20high-altitude%20Depsang%20plains%20remain%20a%20major%20source%20of%20concern%20for%20New%20Delhi%20since%20Chinese%20forces%20continue%20to%20prevent%20Indian%20soldiers%20in%20the%20area%20from%20reaching%20their%20pre-2020%20patrol%20routes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20military-to-military%20talks%20on%20de-escalation%20may%20continue%2C%20China's%20decision%20to%20invest%20in%20hardened%20military%20complexes%20in%20close%20proximity%20to%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20appears%20to%20indicate%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bdigging%20in%20for%20the%20long%20haul%26quot%3B.%20Jeff%20Smith%2C%20Director%20of%20the%20Asian%20Study%20Centre%2C%20who%20has%20seen%20the%20images%20in%20this%20report%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BBeijing%20seems%20determined%20to%20double%20down%20on%20a%20more%20aggressive%20LAC%20strategy%2C%20despite%20the%20considerable%2C%20perhaps%20irreversible%2C%20damage%20it%20has%20done%20to%20its%20relationship%20with%20India%20and%20despite%20facing%20considerable%20headwinds%20with%20a%20cratering%20economy%2C%20an%20accelerating%20rivalry%20with%20the%20U.S%20and%20an%20intensification%20of%20disputes%20in%20the%20Western%20Pacific.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22h6gb3it8%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fh6gb3it8_maxar-satellite-aksai-chin_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExtensive%20Chinese%20military%20construction%20activity%20in%20Aksai%20Chin%20indicates%20Beijing's%20willingness%20to%20be%20permanently%20deployed%20in%20frontline%20areas%C2%A0(High%20res%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F%253ca%2520href%3D%2522https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fn0qsje6g_maxar-satellite-aksai-chin-hd-5_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%2522%253ehere%253c%2Fa%253e%5C%22%3EClick%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20high-resolution%20pic)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202020%2C%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20soldiers%20clashed%20at%20multiple%20locations%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20in%20Northeast%20Ladakh%20resulting%20in%20the%20most%20violent%20assaults%20since%20the%201962%20war.%20On%2015%20June%202020%2C%2020%20Indian%20Army%20soldiers%2C%20including%20the%20commanding%20officer%20of%20an%20infantry%20battalion%2C%20were%20killed%20in%20hand-to-hand%20clashes%20in%20the%20Galwan%20Valley.%20The%20true%20number%20of%20Chinese%20casualties%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20significantly%20higher%20than%20the%20four%20deaths%20that%20Beijing%20officially%20accepted%20with%20investigative%20reports%20suggesting%20that%20at%20least%2038%20Chinese%20soldiers%20had%20been%20killed%20in%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%202020%20clashes%2C%20India%20has%20vastly%20accelerated%20road%20and%20tunnel%20construction%20in%20the%20Ladakh%20region%20and%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20modernising%20and%20adapting%20high-altitude%20airfields.%20Significantly%2C%20New%20Delhi%20has%20completed%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Darbuk-Shyok-Daulat%20Beg%20Oldi%20(DSDBO)%20road%2C%20which%20connects%20Leh%20with%20the%20sensitive%20Daulat%20Beg%20Oldie%20(DBO)%20post%20near%20the%20LAC.%20The%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20flies%20transport%20aircraft%20to%20DBO.%20The%20new%20road%20access%20means%20that%20both%20the%20base%20and%20soldiers%20deployed%20in%20the%20sensitive%20area%20can%20be%20maintained%20through%20a%20road%20line%20that%20has%20reduced%20travel%20time%20from%20two%20days%20to%20six%20hours.%20A%20new%20tunnel%20is%20also%20being%20constructed%20on%20this%20route.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693327920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fipq12b6g_maxar-satellite-aksai-chin-1200_625x300_29_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchina-goes-underground-in-aksai-chin-what-it-means-for-indian-forces-4340185%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sixty%20kilometres%20east%20of%20the%20Depsang%20Plains%20in%20Northern%20Ladakh%2C%20Chinese%20forces%20have%20begun%20carving%20tunnels%20and%20shafts%20into%20a%20hillside%20along%20a%20narrow%20river%20valley%20to%20construct%20multiple%20reinforced%20shelters%20and%20bunkers%20for%20soldiers%20and%20weaponry.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchina-goes-underground-in-aksai-chin-what-it-means-for-indian-forces-4340185%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchina-goes-underground-in-aksai-chin-what-it-means-for-indian-forces-4340185%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchina-goes-underground-in-aksai-chin-what-it-means-for-indian-forces-4340185%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Actors%20who%20played%20lovers%20%26amp%3B%20siblings%20on%20screen%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693326504000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103183470%2Cimgsize-73878.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainme