27%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Elightly%20for%20style%2C%20syntax%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELast%20week%2C%20India%20celebrated%2076%20years%20of%20independence%2C%20but%20many%20in%20our%20country%20are%20still%20looking%20for%20independence%20from%20caste%20prejudice%20and%20discrimination.%20Today%20at%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20we%20are%20being%20joined%20by%20Manoj%20Mitta.%20He%20is%20a%20former%20journalist%20and%20now%20a%20writer.%20He%20has%20written%20two%20books%2C%20and%20he%20comes%20to%20us%20with%20his%20third%20book%2C%20which%20is%20called%20%3Cem%3ECaste%20Pride%3A%20Battles%20for%20Equality%20in%20Hindu%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20would%20say%20that%20this%20is%20essential%20reading%20for%20anybody%20who%20wishes%20to%20understand%20India%E2%80%99s%20trajectory%20with%20caste%2C%20and%20how%20the%20battle%20for%20legal%20equality%20has%20played%20out%20from%20colonial%20times%20till%20now.%20This%20book%20is%20vast.%20It%E2%80%99s%20extensive%2C%20but%20I%20would%20urge%20our%20readers%20to%20read%20it%2C%20because%20it%20is%20essential%20to%20our%20understanding%20of%20the%20legal%20history%20along%20with%20the%20political%20history%20of%20where%20India%20is%20today%20in%20terms%20of%20caste.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThank%20you%20so%20much%2C%20Manoj%2C%20for%20joining%20us%20at%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThanks%2C%20Sravasti%2C%20for%20your%20generous%20introduction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FPfgUZsBzQuU%3Fsi%3DWtM2g9KzMtNTjefA%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20my%20first%20question%20to%20you%2C%20as%20the%20book%20suggests%2C%20is%20on%20the%20battles%20for%20equality%20in%20Hindu%20India%2C%20and%20it%20kind%20of%20traverses%20India%E2%80%99s%20legal%20and%20political%20history%20for%20over%20200%20years.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%2C%20you%20have%20written%20two%20books%20in%20the%20past%3A%20one%20was%20on%20the%20Sikh%20riots%2C%20one%20was%20on%20the%20Gujarat%20riots%20in%202002.%20What%20made%20you%20choose%20caste%20as%20the%20topic%20of%20your%20third%20book%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20said%2C%20I%20dealt%20with%20two%20egregious%20instances%20of%20mass%20violence%2C%20and%20what%20I%20was%20originally%20planning%20to%20do%20was%20complete%20a%20trilogy%20on%20mass%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20focus%20on%20mass%20violence%20targeting%20Dalits%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20explore%20this%20question%3A%20Why%20is%20there%20so%20much%20impunity%20for%20such%20instances%20of%20mass%20violence%20despite%20a%20special%20law%2C%20you%20know%2C%20unlike%20in%20the%20case%20of%20communal%20violence%20where%20there%20is%20no%20special%20enactment%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20violence%20or%20atrocities%20committed%20against%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%2C%20there%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20law%2C%20and%20a%20law%20that%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20rather%20stringent%20%E2%80%93%20and%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20some%2C%20even%20draconian%20%E2%80%93%20and%20so%20my%20question%20was%20why%20is%20there%20so%20much%20impunity%20for%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20I%20looked%20at%20some%20of%20those%20instances%2C%20you%20know%2C%20examined%20the%20judgments%2C%20looked%20at%20the%20prosecution%20documents%20and%20so%20on%20and%20so%20forth%2C%20I%20was%20struck%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20again%20and%20again%20I%E2%80%99m%20coming%20up%20with%2C%20I%20mean%E2%80%A6%20I%E2%80%99m%20confronted%20by%20this%20pattern%20of%20some%20arm%20or%20the%20other%20of%20the%20Indian%20state%20betraying%20caste%20prejudice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20other%20way%20of%20interpreting%20it%2C%20given%20the%20kind%20of%20specious%20grounds%20on%20which%20instances%20of%20such%20magnitude%2C%20you%20know%2C%20crimes%20of%20such%20magnitude%20resulted%20in%20acquittals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20%E2%80%A6%20it%20could%20be%20the%20police%20that%20did%20the%20cause%20of%20justice%20in%2C%20or%20it%20could%20be%20the%20prosecution%2C%20or%20in%20some%20instances%2C%20the%20trial%20court%2C%20or%20it%20could%20even%20be%20the%20appellate%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20understand%20where%20was%20this%20kind%20of%20institutional%20bias%20or%20structural%20bias%20coming%20from%2C%20and%20that%20made%20me%20go%20into%20earlier%20debates%2C%20beginning%20with%2C%20say%2C%20the%20debate%20in%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20over%20the%20abolition%20of%20untouchability.%20And%20then%20there%20were%20references%20to%20what%20happened%20during%20the%20colonial%20period%2C%20because%20after%20all%20what%20was%20happening%20in%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20was%20a%20legacy%20of%20those%20unfinished%20battles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20one%20thing%20led%20to%20another%20and%20I%20found%20myself%20unearthing%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20hitherto%20unseen%20material%20from%20legislatures%20and%20courts%2C%20going%20all%20the%20way%20back%20to%20%5Bthe%5D%20early%2019th%20century.%20So%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20over%20200%20years%20and%20different%20aspects%20of%20caste%20reforms%2C%20and%20they%20were%20most%20revealing%20%E2%80%A6%20not%20just%20about%20the%20situation%20in%20India%20at%20that%20time%20of%20the%20colonial%20rule%2C%20but%20also%20it%20helps%20you%20understand%20many%20of%20today%E2%80%99s%20fault%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20that%20was%20the%20spirit%20in%20which%20I%20expanded%20the%20ambit%20of%20my%20book%20from%20merely%20focusing%20on%20violence%20to%2C%20you%20know%2C%20where%20this%20prejudice%20was%20coming%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERight%2C%20so%20you%20spoke%20about%20how%E2%80%A6%20in%20the%20book%2C%20you%20talk%20about%20how%20caste%20has%20informed%20legal%20punishments%20and%20legal%20reforms%20throughout%20colonial%20history%20until%20now.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20in%20the%20book%2C%20you%20talk%20about%20how%20the%20British%2C%20in%20their%20bid%20to%20win%20over%20the%20upper%20caste%20%E2%80%93%20who%20were%20essentially%20the%20men%20in%20power%20%E2%80%93%20gave%20penal%20provisions%20an%20Indian%20twist.%20Now%2C%20two%20things%20stood%20out%20to%20me%20in%20this%20regard%3A%20one%20was%20the%20punishment%20of%20confinement%20to%20the%20stocks%20and%20the%20other%20was%20the%20exemption%20of%20the%20Banaras%20Brahmins%20from%20the%20death%20penalty.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECould%20you%20talk%20to%20us%20a%20little%20bit%20about%20these%20penalties%20and%20how%20the%20British%20gave%20it%20an%20Indian%20twist%2C%20as%20you%20call%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20so%20before%20I%20go%20into%20the%20details%20of%20that%2C%20one%20needs%20to%20put%20that%20in%20context.%20We%20are%20now%20talking%20about%20that%20early%20phase%20of%20colonial%20rule%2C%20after%20all%20%E2%80%A6%20colonial%20rule%20is%20said%20to%20have%20begun%20after%20the%20Battle%20of%20Plassey%20in%201757.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20are%20talking%20about%20the%20early%20decades%2C%20and%20this%20was%20a%20time%20when%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20understand%20our%20society%2C%20our%20culture%2C%20our%20religion%2C%20and%20they%20began%20to%20do%20these%20translations%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20it%20was%20then%20their%20understanding%20that%20given%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20were%20in%20one%20huge%20country%20and%20they%20were%20so%20few%20in%20number%2C%20one%20way%20they%20thought%20they%20could%20run%20the%20country%20%E2%80%93%20control%20these%20masses%20%E2%80%93%20was%20through%20the%20elite%2C%20by%20co-opting%20the%20elite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20first%20thing%20they%20did%20was%20that%20in%201795%2C%20they%20came%20up%20with%20this%2C%20I%20mean%2C%20among%20other%20measures%2C%20it%20took%20the%20form%20of%20this%20enactment%2C%20this%20law%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20departure%20from%20their%20above%20principle%20of%20equality%2C%20they%20exempt%20Brahmins%2C%20and%20among%20Brahmins%20particularly%20Banaras%20Brahmins%2C%20because%20they%20were%20considered%20the%20most%20sacrosanct%2C%20Banaras%20being%20the%20holiest%20of%20holy%20cities.%20So%20they%20exempt%20Banaras%20Brahmins%20from%20the%20death%20penalty%20irrespective%20of%20what%20crime%20they%20were%20found%20to%20have%20committed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20in%20keeping%20with%20this%20notion%2C%20this%20traditional%20notion%2C%20that%20Brahmins%20cannot%20be%20killed%20for%20any%20reason%20whatsoever%20because%20that%20would%20amount%20to%20%3Cem%3Ebrahmahatya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20for%20which%20there%20is%20no%20remedy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20even%20somebody%20like%20Lord%20Ram%20was%20not%20exempted%2C%20when%20he%20killed%20Ravan%20%E2%80%93%20Ravan%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20Brahmin%2C%20while%20Ram%20was%20merely%20a%20Kshatriya%2C%20which%20is%20a%20rung%20lower%20than%20Brahmins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20they%20very%20wilfully%2C%20very%20astutely%2C%20they%20decide%20to%20%E2%80%93%20or%20%E2%80%9Castutely%E2%80%9D%20in%20quotes%20%E2%80%93%20incorporate%20that%20in%20their%20system%20of%20law%20and%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20thankfully%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20long%3A%20about%20two%20decades%20later%20or%20so%2C%20they%20realised%20their%20folly%20and%20%5Bdid%5D%20away%20with%20it%2C%20they%20repealed%20that%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20this%2C%20or%20around%20the%20time%20this%20enactment%20relating%20to%20you%20know%20exempting%20Brahmins%20from%20the%20death%20penalty%20is%20repealed%2C%20and%20somebody%20in%E2%80%A6%20this%20happens%20in%20Calcutta%2C%20Bengal%20Presidency%2C%20the%20law%20relating%20to%20Brahmins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20in%20the%20Madras%20Presidency%2C%20somebody%20who%20went%20on%20to%20become%20Governor%20of%20Madras%2C%20Thomas%20Munro%2C%20when%20he%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20drafting%20laws%20for%20that%20presidency%2C%20came%20up%20with%20this%20idea%20of%20co-opting%20something%20from%20the%20Western%20tradition%2C%20which%20is%20this%20very%20corporal%2C%20very%20barbaric%20form%20of%20punishment%2C%20called%20confinement%20in%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20references%20to%20it%20in%20the%20Bible%2C%20in%20Shakespeare%E2%80%99s%20literature%2C%20and%20in%20fact%2C%20that%20is%20the%20origin%20of%20that%20famous%20term%20%E2%80%98laughing%20stock%E2%80%99%2C%20you%20know%2C%20so%20this%20is%20about%20a%20convicted%20person%20being%20subjected%20to%20ridicule%2C%20he%20is%20put%20in%20a%20public%20place%20and%20his%20feet%20would%20be%20clamped%20to%20a%20wooden%20frame%20with%20holes%2C%20and%20he%20would%20be%20flung%20with%20all%20sorts%20of%20things%2C%20spat%20upon%20and%20stuff%20like%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20dehumanising%20punishment%20and%20that%20was%20typically%20reserved%20for%20the%20underclass%20in%20the%20West%2C%20you%20know%2C%20the%20labour%20that%20was%20errant%20and%20had%20to%20be%20punished%2C%20so%20this%20was%20how%20they%20dealt%20with%20it.%20And%20Munro%2C%20very%20perversely%2C%20thought%2C%20%E2%80%98Okay%2C%20why%20don%E2%80%99t%20I%20bring%20that%20here%20into%20the%20Indian%20milieu%20and%20use%20it%20against%20the%20lower%20caste%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20instance%20indeed%20%5Bwhen%5D%20this%20expression%20%E2%80%98lower%20caste%E2%80%99%20was%20actually%20put%20into%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERight.%20So%20the%20book%20also%20provides%20a%20very%20interesting%20insight%20into%20the%20intersectionality%20of%20caste%20and%20patriarchy.%20In%20various%20ways%2C%20we%20see%20not%20only%20women%20from%20the%20lower%20caste%E2%80%A6%20they%20are%20obviously%20worse%20off%20because%20of%20their%20caste%2C%20but%20they%20get%20the%20absolute%20end%20of%20the%20stick%20because%20they%20are%20also%20women.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20example%20of%20this%2C%20which%20is%20very%20interesting%2C%20was%20about%20the%20women%20in%20Travancore%20who%20were%20not%20allowed%20to%20cover%20their%20breasts%20in%20public.%20So%2C%20could%20you%20tell%20us%20about%20this%20incident%20and%20how%20this%20came%20about%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20this%20was%20actually%20a%20bizarre%20fallout%20of%20Queen%20Victoria%E2%80%99s%20Proclamation%20of%201858.%20This%20was%20in%20turn%20a%20sequel%20to%20the%20Great%20Revolt%20of%201857%2C%20and%20as%20you%20know%2C%20it%20also%20marked%20the%20transition%20from%20East%20India%20Company%20%5Brule%5D%20to%20India%20being%20directly%20ruled%20by%20the%20British%20Crown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20at%20that%20time%20during%20that%20period%20of%20transition%2C%20she%20made%20this%20proclamation%20and%20reaffirmed%20the%20British%20commitment%20to%2C%20you%20know%2C%20being%20very%20mindful%20of%20people%E2%80%99s%20religious%20feelings%2C%20and%20she%20undertakes%20that%20there%20would%20be%20no%20attempt%20to%20interfere%20with%20them%2C%20because%20after%20all%2C%20if%20you%20recall%2C%20the%201857%20revolt%20was%20triggered%20by%20this%20perception%20that%2C%20you%20know%2C%20there%20was%20some%20fat%20made%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%A6%20Cartridge%2C%20which%20offended%20the%20Hindus%20and%20the%20Muslims%20for%20different%20reasons.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20this%20perception%20that%20it%20was%20either%20from%20pigs%20or%20from%20cows.%20So%2C%20mindful%20as%20they%20were%20of%20that%20backdrop%2C%20they%20made%20that%20reaffirmation%20again%2C%20and%20that%20%E2%80%A6%20when%20it%20was%20translated%20into%20Malayalam%20in%20Travancore%2C%20which%20was%20a%20princely%20state%2C%20they%20interpreted%20that%20to%20mean%20that%2C%20%E2%80%98Okay%2C%20since%20they%20are%20not%20going%20to%20interfere%20with%20our%20customs%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%A6%20they%20took%20it%20as%20a%20license%20to%20bring%20back%20certain%20practices%20which%20were%20already%20repealed%20due%20to%20efforts%20made%20by%20some%20reformers%20and%20because%20of%20intervention%20by%20the%20British%20administration%2C%20you%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20had%20this%20very%20curious%20and%20instructive%20situation%20where%20the%20dominant%20caste%2C%20the%20Nairs%2C%20in%20collusion%20with%20the%20%3Cem%3Ediwan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Madhav%20Rao%2C%20who%20was%20a%20Marathi-speaking%20Brahmin%20from%20Tanjore%20in%20Madras%20Presidency%2C%20and%20the%20king%20of%20Travancore%2C%20they%20all%20came%20together%20and%20decided%2C%20%E2%80%98Okay%2C%20since%20there%20is%20such%20a%20demand%20being%20made%20by%20the%20dominant%20caste%2C%20we%20will%20not%20let%20women%20of%20lower%20caste%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%A6%20namely%20Nadar%2C%20who%20were%20showing%20signs%20of%2C%20you%20know%2C%20some%20equality%2C%20assertions%20of%20equality%2C%20because%20they%20had%20been%20exposed%20to%20education%2C%20there%20was%20also%20an%20influence%20of%20Christian%20missionaries%2C%20many%20of%20them%20had%20converted%2C%20and%20they%20had%20taken%20to%20entrepreneurship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20because%20of%20the%20stigma%20of%20their%20caste%20being%20associated%2C%20traditionally%2C%20with%20toddy%20tapping%2C%20they%20were%20looked%20down%20upon.%20And%20one%20must%20also%20bear%20in%20mind%20that%20in%20the%20South%2C%20including%20Travancore%2C%20it%20was%20not%20just%20untouchability%20%E2%80%93%20what%20was%20practiced%20there%20was%20also%20%E2%80%98unapproachability%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20they%20came%20up%20with%20this%20diabolical%20device%2C%20a%20proclamation%2C%20drawing%20inspiration%20from%2C%20very%20erroneously%20of%20course%2C%20from%20Victoria%E2%80%99s%20proclamation%2C%20saying%20that%20women%20of%20the%20Nadar%20community%20will%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20cover%20their%20breasts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%3F%20Because%20if%20they%20were%20if%20they%20were%20allowed%20to%20do%20so%2C%20then%20they%20would%20be%20indistinguishable%20from%20women%20from%20upper%20castes%2C%20and%20for%20them%20it%20was%20important%20to%20know%2C%20from%20a%20distance%2C%20you%20need%20to%20know%20whether%20those%20people%20were%20from%20this%20caste%20or%20that%20caste%2C%20because%20there%20were%20very%20strict%20rules%20about%20how%20much%20distance%20each%20caste%20had%20to%20maintain%20from%20the%20caste%20that%20was%20above%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20all%20very%20instructive%20to%20see%20how%20caste%20was%20such%20a%20non-negotiable%2C%20such%20an%20overriding%20concern%20for%20us.%20I%20mean%20this%20is%20irrespective%20of%20the%20colonial%20rule%3B%20and%20if%20anything%2C%20colonial%20rule%20was%20not%20the%20villain%20of%20the%20piece%20here%2C%20it%20was%20our%20own%2C%20you%20know%2C%20obscurantist%20notions%20that%20we%20were%20carrying%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20these%20are%20not%20things%20that%20the%20British%20were%20introducing%20in%20our%20heads%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20something%20that%20we%20had%20and%20we%20were%20negotiating.%20Those%20of%20us%20who%20were%20in%20those%20dominant%20positions%20were%20negotiating%20with%20the%20British%20in%20order%20to%20perpetuate%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20then%2C%20beyond%20a%20point%2C%20they%20could%20not%20tolerate%20that%2C%20because%20there%20was%20a%20pushback%20from%20lower%20castes%2C%20from%20the%20affected%20castes%2C%20and%20they%20tried%20to%20be%20fair%20and%20they%20intervened%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20alleviated%20the%20situation%20to%20an%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYeah.%20So%20you%20have%20been%20mentioning%20this%2C%20and%20as%20we%20are%20still%20on%20the%20topic%20of%20intersectionality%20of%20caste%20and%20patriarchy%2C%20another%20case%20in%20point%20that%20illustrates%20this%20further%2C%20as%20you%20were%20mentioning%20earlier%2C%20was%20the%20fight%20to%20abolish%20sati.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20here%20we%20find%2C%20as%20you%20were%20saying%2C%20an%20unlikely%20villain%E2%80%A6%20in%20the%20book%2C%20we%20find%20out%20that%20the%20unlikely%20villain%20is%20Motilal%20Nehru%2C%20who%20was%20found%20to%20be%20defending%20sati%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20upper%20castes.%20If%20you%20could%20tell%20us%20a%20little%20bit%20about%20this%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20was%20his%20backstory%3F%20What%20did%20he%20do%20when%20he%20was%20not%20yet%20such%20a%20big%20leader%2C%20when%20he%20was%20a%20prominent%20member%20of%20the%20Bar%20in%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20takes%20up%20a%20case%20in%20which%20some%20four%20or%20five%20persons%20were%20already%20convicted%20in%20a%20case%20of%20sati%2C%20%5Bhaving%20had%20their%20plea%20rejected%5D%20that%20they%20were%20not%20to%20blame%20because%20the%20pyre%20lit%20on%20its%20own%20%E2%80%93%20a%20spontaneous%20combustion%20took%20place%20%E2%80%93%20because%20of%20the%20sheer%20piety%20of%20the%20woman%20who%20was%20committing%20sati.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20plea%20they%20took%20in%20their%20defence%2C%20and%20that%20was%20rejected%20outright%20by%20the%20trial%20court.%20Now%2C%20Motilal%20Nehru%20takes%20up%20this%20case%20at%20the%20appeal%20stage%20and%20reiterates%20that%20line%20of%20argument%2C%20that%20line%20of%20defence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F06110613%2FMotilalNehru4.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F06110613%2FMotilalNehru4.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F06110613%2FMotilalNehru4-300x175.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F06110613%2FMotilalNehru4-1024x596.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-651934%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22698%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMotilal%20Nehru.%20Photo%3A%20Unknown%20author%2C%20Public%20Domain%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20fightback%20from%20Indians%2C%20Indian%20politicians%2C%20against%20caste%2C%20only%20happened%20when%20some%20sort%20of%20political%20representation%20happened%20for%20Indians%2C%20and%20they%20started%20finding%20themselves%20in%20legislatures%20following%20the%20reforms%20that%20took%20place%20around%20that%20time.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20this%20change%20happen%2C%20and%20how%20did%20Indians%20finally%20start%20bringing%20bills%20to%20change%20the%20caste%20hierarchy%20and%20the%20system%20of%20discrimination%20through%20legal%20reforms%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESee%2C%20Indian%20representation%20began%2C%20you%20know%2C%20way%20back%20in%201861%20%E2%80%93%20this%20was%2C%20after%20all%2C%20the%20change%20that%20took%20place%20post%20the%20revolt%20and%20post%20the%20entry%20of%20the%20Crown%20(the%20Crown%20was%20directly%20ruling%20us%2C%20right).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20in%20those%20early%20decades%2C%20the%20few%20Indians%20who%20were%20there%20in%20those%20legislatures%20were%20essentially%20big%20landlords%2C%20%3Cem%3Ezamindars%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20big%20rulers%20themselves%2C%20so%20they%20were%20not%20likely%20to%20have%20any%20truck%20with%20issues%20concerning%20social%20reform%20or%20anything%20of%20that%20sort.%20They%20were%20very%20deeply%20orthodox%20in%20their%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20things%20got%20better%20as%20%5Bmore%20and%20more%20constitutional%20reforms%20were%20made%5D%20and%20by%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century%2C%20you%20had%20people%20like%2C%20say%E2%80%A6%20somebody%20who%20was%20considered%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20and%20Jinnah%E2%80%99s%20mentor%2C%20that%20is%20Gokhale%2C%20entering%2C%20people%20who%20had%20their%20background%20in%20Congress%20discussions%20and%20meetings.%20So%2C%20they%20were%20members%20of%20this%2C%20and%20that%20did%20increase%20the%20quality%20of%20discussions%20and%20interventions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20you%20know%2C%20not%20until%201916%20was%20the%20issue%20of%20something%20as%20egregious%20as%20untouchability%20%5Btaken%20up%5D%20in%20that%20House%2C%20and%20when%20it%20was%2C%20when%20the%20silence%20on%20untouchability%20was%20finally%20broken%2C%20it%20was%20not%20because%20of%20any%20of%20the%20prominent%20leaders%20with%20Congress%20background%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20somebody%20who%20was%20very%20little%20known%20and%20who%20was%20not%20even%20a%20Hindu.%20His%20name%20was%20Maneckji%20Dadabhoy%2C%20not%20to%20be%20mistaken%20with%20Dadabhai%20Naoroji.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201920s%2C%20at%20a%20time%20when%2C%20because%20of%20the%20non-cooperation%20call%20made%20by%20Gandhi%20in%201920%2C%20Congress%20had%20actually%20boycotted%20these%20legislative%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20subsequent%20years%2C%20a%20breakaway%20group%20of%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20form%20of%20the%20Swaraj%20Party%20did%20participate%2C%20and%20it%20was%20in%20order%20to%20fill%20that%20void%20that%2C%20you%20know%2C%20Justice%20Party%20came%20in%20in%20a%20big%20way%2C%20and%20they%20came%20into%20power%20in%20Madras%20and%20they%20initiated%20certain%20reforms.%20They%20were%20the%20ones%20who%20came%20up%20with%20this%20measure%20of%20affirmative%20action%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20British%20India%20in%20the%2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20this%20is%20how%20things%20unfolded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYeah.%20So%2C%20you%20were%20mentioning%20earlier%20about%20how%20the%20Congress%20did%20not%20really%E2%80%A6%20it%20was%20a%20big%20tent%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20a%20big%20tent%2C%20as%20you%20mentioned%20and%20there%20were%20all%20kinds%20of%20leaders.%20So%20we%20had%20a%20Madan%20Mohan%20Malaviya%2C%20we%20also%20had%20a%20Vithalbhai%20Patel%2C%20so%20we%20had%20various%20kinds%20of%20leaders%20from%20the%20Congress%20and%20you%20have%20written%20about%2C%20and%20also%20you%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20about%20how%20political%20reforms%20found%20precedence%20over%20social%20reforms%20for%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20this%20is%20very%20interesting%2C%20if%20you%20could%20tell%20us%20a%20little%20bit%20about%20how%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Congress%20evolved%20from%20the%20%E2%80%9820s%20onwards%2C%20where%20earlier%2C%20as%20you%20mentioned%2C%20that%20Dadabhai%20Naoroji%20had%20said%20very%20clearly%20in%20the%201800s%20that%20the%20Congress%20will%20not%20be%20talking%20about%20social%20reforms%20at%20this%20point%20and%20%E2%80%98let%E2%80%99s%20just%20focus%20on%20the%20political%20agenda%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20later%2C%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9820s%20onwards%2C%20things%20started%20to%20change%20within%20the%20Congress%20itself%20and%20the%20fight%20started%20focusing%20on%20that%20as%20well%2C%20so%20if%20you%20could%20tell%20us%20about%20the%20evolving%20role%20of%20the%20Congress%20from%20the%20%E2%80%9820s%20onwards%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20this%20was%20a%20struggle%20that%20preceded%20colonial%20rule%20and%20also%20survived%20the%20end%20of%20the%20colonial%20rule%2C%20the%20decolonisation%20of%20India.%20And%20it%20is%20still%20there%20with%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhereas%20colonial%20rule%20ended%2C%20as%20you%20said%20at%20the%20beginning%2C%20in%201947%20%E2%80%93%20we%20celebrated%20the%2076th%20anniversary%20of%20that%2C%20right%3F%20Whereas%2C%20there%20is%20no%20such%20anniversary%20of%20the%20end%20of%20these%20social%20struggles%2C%20because%20those%20struggles%20never%20ended%2C%20and%20Congress%20took%20a%20long%20while%20to%20realise%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20tussle%20going%20on%20in%20the%20Congress.%20There%20were%20these%20battles%20that%20were%20being%20fought%20in%20the%20Congress%20and%20outside%2C%20in%20the%20larger%20Indian%20society%20during%20the%20colonial%20rule%2C%20on%20this%20issue%20of%20caste%2C%20and%20they%20were%20not%20necessarily%20between%20upper%20castes%20and%20lower%20castes.%20They%20were%20between%20two%20sets%20of%20Hindus%3A%20the%20progressive%2C%20liberal%20Hindus%20on%20one%20side%2C%20and%20these%20orthodox%2C%20obscurantist%20Hindus%20on%20the%20other%20side%2C%20who%20would%20not%20hesitate%20to%20cite%20all%20sorts%20of%20reasons%20relating%20to%20custom%20or%20even%20religion%2C%20they%20would%20quote%20scriptures%20to%20defend%20the%20most%20untenable%20practices%20that%20were%20in%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20mean%20for%20the%20kind%20of%20arguments%2C%20say%2C%20somebody%20like%20Malaviya%20gave%20for%20opposing%20the%20inter-caste%20marriage%20Bill%20initiated%20by%20Vithalbhai%20Patel.%20So%2C%20likewise%2C%20you%20would%20see%20somebody%20like%20Gandhi%20also%20taking%20very%20long%20to%20understand%E2%80%A6%20for%20his%20own%20understanding%20to%20evolve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%201920s%2C%20you%20know%2C%20by%201920%2C%20he%20had%20in%20a%20sense%20captured%20the%20Congress%20party%2C%20he%20became%20the%20unchallenged%20leader%20of%20that%20party%2C%20right%3F%20So%20through%20those%20%E2%80%9920s%2C%20he%20was%20also%20a%20votary%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Evarna%3C%2Fem%3E%20system%2C%20although%20formally%20he%20had%20right%20in%20the%201920%20Nagpur%20Congress%20resolutions%E2%80%A6%20%5Bhe%5D%20was%20instrumental%20in%20making%20a%20resolution%20against%20untouchability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20it%20%5Bdid%5D%20not%20translate%20into%20anything%20radical%20like%2C%20%E2%80%98Okay%2C%20we%20will%20now%20throw%20open%20all%20these%20public%20amenities%20to%20Dalits%2C%20we%20will%20now%20throw%20open%20temples%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20you%20know%2C%20that%20%5Btemples%5D%20were%20considered%20an%20even%20more%20challenging%2C%20even%20more%20sensitive%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20it%20was%20not%20until%2C%20say%2C%201932%2C%20the%20Poona%20Pact%2C%20in%20which%20depressed%20classes%2C%20most%20importantly%20somebody%20like%20Ambedkar%2C%20%5Bwere%5D%20forced%20to%20give%20up%20their%20hard-fought%20right%20to%20a%20separate%20electorate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20when%20as%20a%20result%20of%20that%20Poona%20Pact%2C%20when%20Gandhi%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20make%20a%20reciprocal%20gesture%2C%20so%20there%20were%20certain%20resolutions%20that%20were%20passed%20by%20his%20followers%20in%20Bombay%2C%20just%20a%20day%20after%20the%20Poona%20Pact%2C%20and%20one%20of%20them%20related%20to%20temple%20entry%2C%20and%20bit%20by%20bit%20as%20his%20own%20understanding%20got%20better%2C%20he%20opens%20up%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20Dalits%2C%20who%20were%20then%20called%20depressed%20classes%2C%20he%20began%20(around%20that%20time)%20referring%20to%20them%20as%20%3Cem%3EHarijans.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20he%20opened%20up%20to%20that%2C%20but%20even%20then%20it%20was%20in%20a%20very%20incremental%20manner.%20It%20was%20not%20in%20the%20sense%20in%20which%20Ambedkar%E2%80%A6%20in%201929%2C%20Ambedkar%20had%20drafted%20a%20Bill%20which%20adopted%20a%20rights-based%20approach%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20across%20the%20board%20in%20all%20temples%2C%20all%20Hindus%20irrespective%20of%20caste%2C%20and%20certainly%20including%20%3Cem%3Eavarnas%3C%2Fem%3E%20(untouchables)%2C%20they%20would%20be%20given%20access%20to%20temples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201929%2C%20Ambedkar%20took%20that%20position%2C%20and%20in%201933%2C%20when%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20eyes%20opened%20to%20the%20need%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20temple%20entry%20issue%2C%20he%20does%20not%20adopt%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20rights-based%20approach.%20What%20he%20adopts%20is%20what%20he%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98local%20option%E2%80%99%20approach%2C%20which%20is%20that%20you%20go%20and%20conduct%20a%20referendum%20in%20a%20given%20temple%20%E2%80%A6%20you%20take%20it%20up%20on%20a%20case-by-case%20basis%2C%20so%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20question%20of%20%5Ball%20temples%20being%20opened%20up%20overnight%5D%2C%20most%20certainly%20not%20those%20ones%20which%20have%20a%20long%20history%2C%20you%20know%2C%20which%20are%20considered%20very%20sacrosanct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20he%20said%20%E2%80%98if%20there%20is%20some%20temple%20somewhere%20which%20wants%20to%20open%20up%2C%20you%20conduct%20a%20referendum%20among%20the%20local%20devotees%2C%20and%20if%20they%20are%20in%20favour%20of%20it%2C%20that%20temple%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20temple%20alone%20%E2%80%93%20will%20be%20opened.%20And%20likewise%20you%20conduct%20a%20referendum%20in%20another%20one%E2%80%99.%20He%20actually%20backs%20a%20Bill%20that%20was%20introduced%20at%20that%20time%20by%20one%20Ranga%20Iyer%20in%20the%20Central%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20those%20are%20the%20kind%20of%20efforts%20being%20made%2C%20you%20know%20through%20those%20%E2%80%9830s.%20It%20was%20very%20half-hearted%2C%20it%20was%20not%20something%20which%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98No%2C%20Untouchables%20or%20whoever%20was%20considered%20Untouchable%20cannot%20be%20stopped%20from%20entering%20temples%20because%20they%20are%20as%20much%20Hindus%20as%20Brahmins%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20he%20was%20not%20willing%20to%20go%20that%20far.%20He%20was%20willing%20to%20do%20it%20in%20a%20very%20incremental%20manner.%20As%20a%20mass%20leader%2C%20his%20compulsion%20was%20to%20be%20not%20too%20far%20ahead%20of%20public%20opinion.%20In%20his%20own%20personal%20life%2C%20he%20was%20quite%20radical%3A%20in%20his%20own%20ashram%2C%20he%20would%20not%20follow%20any%20of%20these%20varna%20rules%2C%20he%20would%20himself%20participate%20in%20the%20task%20of%20cleaning%20toilets%2C%20and%20so%20on%20and%20so%20forth.%20He%20would%20adopt%20a%20Dalit%20girl%20as%20his%20daughter%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20his%20public%20persona%2C%20he%20was%20different.%20He%20was%20forced%20to%20be%20very%20cautious%20and%20appear%20very%20conservative%20so%20that%20he%20did%20not%20appear%20too%20reckless%20or%20too%20radical.%20So%2C%20this%20dichotomy%20you%20see%20in%20Gandhi%20is%20all%20very%20fascinating%20to%20discover.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20dichotomy%20in%20Gandhi%2C%20which%20you%20have%20referred%20to%20in%20the%20book%20as%20%E2%80%9CGandhi%E2%80%99s%20balancing%20act%E2%80%9D%2C%20was%20basically%20his%20bid%20to%20woo%20people%E2%80%99s%20hearts%20and%20he%20did%20not%20want%20to%20take%20any%20radical%20steps.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20a%20very%20contrasting%20approach%20was%20taken%20by%20Ambedkar%2C%20and%20any%20discussion%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20fight%20against%20caste%20obviously%20cannot%20be%20complete%20without%20discussing%20Ambedkar.%20So%20you%20have%20written%20about%20how%20the%20two%20had%20a%20couple%20of%20differences%20about%20approaching%20the%20issues%20of%E2%80%A6%20whether%20it%20was%20temple%20entry%20or%20how%20depressed%20classes%20would%20get%20representation.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20you%20could%20tell%20us%20how%20these%20differences%20kind%20of%20played%20out%20and%20what%20were%20their%20positions%20on%20which%20they%E2%80%A6%20while%20Ambedkar%20was%20seen%20more%20of%20a%20radical%20in%20that%20sense%2C%20Gandhi%20was%20more%20of%20a%20moderate.%20So%20if%20you%20could%20explain%20that%20a%20little%20bit%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESee%2C%20they%20had%20their%20own%20trajectories%2C%20their%20own%20learning%20curve%2C%20so%20to%20say.%20During%20the%20%E2%80%9820s%2C%20Ambedkar%20was%20not%20anywhere%20as%20radical%20as%20he%20was%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9830s%2C%20you%20know.%20He%20was%20quite%20keen%20on%20exploring%20the%20possibility%20of%20finding%20an%20honourable%2C%20dignified%20place%20for%20Dalits%20within%20the%20Hindu%20fold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20step%20was%2C%20as%20I%20said%2C%20the%201929%20Bill%20that%20he%20drafted%2C%20and%20then%2C%20the%20following%20year%2C%20he%20himself%20led%20a%20temple%20entry%20movement%20in%20the%20Kalaram%20temple%20in%20Nashik.%20And%20that%20proved%20to%20be%20quite%20a%20turning%20point%20for%20him%2C%20because%20he%20sees%20the%20vehemence%20with%20which%20Hindus%2C%20conservative%20Hindus%2C%20push%20back%20against%20it.%20And%20there%20was%20even%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%20was%20not%20the%20first%20time%20he%20was%20seeing%E2%80%A6%20In%201927%2C%20he%20had%20a%20similar%20experience%2C%20that%20was%20in%20Mahad%2C%20with%20respect%20to%20throwing%20open%20a%20lake%2C%20a%20tank%20as%20it%20was%20called%2C%20the%20Chavadar%20Tank%2C%20to%20Dalits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20there%20again%2C%20there%20was%20violence%20and%20so%20on.%20And%20he%20on%20that%20occasion%20does%20go%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20even%20burning%20pages%20from%20Manusmriti%2C%20right%2C%20as%20a%20mark%20of%20protest.%20But%20then%20since%20that%20is%20not%20quite%20considered%20a%20religious%20scripture%20like%2C%20say%2C%20the%20Bhagavad%20Gita%20is%2C%20it%20did%20not%20still%20mean%20that%20he%20had%20given%20up%20on%20Hinduism.%20As%20his%20subsequent%20actions%20showed%2C%20he%20even%20participated%20in%20an%20event%20in%20which%20he%20experimented%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20making%20Dalits%20wear%20a%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ejaneu%20%3C%2Fem%3E(sacred%20thread).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20these%20are%20the%20kinds%20of%20things%20he%20was%20doing%20in%20the%201920s.%20And%20that%20culminated%20in%20that%20temple%20entry%20movement%20in%20Nashik%20and%20the%20reaction%20he%20faced%2C%20the%20opposition%20he%20faced%2C%20disenchanted%20him.%20It%20went%20on%20for%20quite%20some%20time%2C%20but%20you%20know%20while%20he%20was%20negotiating%20with%20Gandhi%20on%20representation%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20it%20should%20be%20a%20separate%20electorate%20or%20joint%20electorate%20and%20stuff%20like%20that%20%E2%80%93%20he%20had%20first%20encountered%20Gandhi%20in%20the%20Second%20Round%20Table%20conference%2C%20and%20then%20that%20led%20to%20the%20McDonald%20Award%20in%20which%20Dalits%20were%20given%20a%20separate%20electorate%2C%20and%20then%20that%20led%20to%20the%20Poona%20Pact%2C%20in%20which%20he%20gives%20up%20that%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20Gandhi%20then%20%E2%80%93%20among%20other%20things%20%E2%80%93%20tries%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20question%20of%20temple%20entry.%20But%20by%20then%2C%20Ambedkar%20had%20moved%20on.%20He%20was%20not%20interested%20in%20temple%20entry%20anymore%20because%20of%20his%20experience%20at%20Nashik.%20He%20was%20now%20more%20focused%20on%20capitalising%20on%20what%20came%20out%20of%20the%20Poona%20Pact%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20that%20there%20will%20not%20be%20a%20separate%20electorate%20but%20there%20will%20be%20electoral%20reservations.%20And%20he%20was%20happy%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20were%20many%20more%20than%20he%20originally%20had%20in%20mind%2C%20that%20were%20reserved%20for%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes.%20That%20term%20was%20yet%20to%20come%20into%20force%2C%20it%20came%20into%20force%20only%20under%20the%2035%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20these%20are%20the%20kind%20of%20trajectories%20that%20they%20were%20going%20through.%20And%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20he%20%5BAmbedkar%5D%20was%20very%20happy%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20Gandhi%20gave%20in%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20reserved%20constituencies.%20Because%20what%20happened%20was%2C%20in%20the%20Round%20Table%20Conference%2C%20Gandhi%20was%20opposed%20to%20not%20just%20a%20separate%20electorate%20but%20he%20said%20no%20question%20of%20even%20reserved%20constituencies.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20leave%20it%20to%20the%20Goodwill%20of%20Hindus%2C%20they%20will%20take%20good%20care%20of%20Untouchables.%E2%80%9D%20So%20that%20was%20a%20position%20that%20he%20had%20taken%20in%20the%20Round%20Table%20Conference.%20And%20Ambedkar%2C%20given%20his%20own%20lived%20experience%20of%20how%20there%20was%20opposition%20to%20any%20kind%20of%20reform%20at%20every%20step%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20that%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20left%20to%20the%20goodwill%20of%20upper%20caste%20Hindus.%20So%20you%20have%20to%20have%20something%20that%20is%20codified%2C%20some%20concession%20has%20to%20be%20made.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20finally%20it%20came%20out%20in%20the%20form%20of%20the%20Poona%20Pact%2C%20in%20which%20they%20met%20halfway.%20Ambedkar%20gives%20up%20on%20his%20%5Bdemand%20for%20a%5D%20separate%20electorate%20and%20then%20Gandhi%20concedes%20on%20reserved%20seats%2C%20which%20is%20a%20system%20that%20we%20still%20have%20and%20the%20origins%20of%20which%20are%20in%20the%20Poona%20Pact.%20In%20the%20initial%20phase%2C%20as%20I%20said%2C%20Ambedkar%20had%20his%20own%20learning%20curve.%20He%20was%20very%20excited.%20He%20thought%20he%20pulled%20off%20a%20great%20coup%2C%20but%20then%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20long%20for%20him%20to%20realise%20that%20these%20reserved%20constituencies%20would%20mean%20that%20only%20those%20Dalits%20who%20were%20acceptable%20to%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20electorate%2C%20which%20is%20caste%20Hindus%20only%20they%20would%20get%20elected.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20as%20if%20a%20radical%20Dalit%20would%20be%20readily%20embraced%20by%20caste%20Hindus%20who%20constitute%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20electorate.%20So%20he%20realised%20that%20%E2%80%93%20and%20he%20was%20very%20disenchanted%20with%20that.%20By%20the%20time%20constitution%20making%20began%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20positions%20he%20had%20begun%20to%20take%20in%20the%20mid-40s%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20to%20get%20back%20to%20a%20separate%20electorate.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20so%20disenchanted%20by%20then%20with%20this%20experiment%20with%20reserved%20constituencies.%20But%20then%2C%20he%20goes%20on%20to%20become%20the%20law%20minister%20of%20the%20country%20and%20then%20become%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Drafting%20Committee.%20So%20all%20those%20positions%20moderate%20his%20own%20opinion%20on%20those%20aspects.%20Finally%2C%20what%20we%20have%20is%20what%20was%20initiated%20by%20the%20Poona%20Pact%2C%20that%20is%20reserved%20constituencies.%20And%20then%20it%20was%20also%20extended%20to%20reservations%20in%20educational%20institutions%20and%20jobs%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F02161041%2Fambedkar-gandhi.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22825%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F02161041%2Fambedkar-gandhi.png%20825w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F02161041%2Fambedkar-gandhi-300x169.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-483160%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22464%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20and%20Mahatma%20Gandhi.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20as%20you%20mentioned%2C%20what%20Ambedkar%20struggled%20to%20get%20in%20terms%20of%20legal%20reforms%20pre-independence%2C%20he%20somewhat%20managed%20to%20get%20post-independence%20because%20of%20the%20positions%20that%20he%20hel%20as%20the%20chairperson%20of%20the%20Drafting%20Committee%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%20But%20finally%2C%20post-independence%2C%20India%20did%20make%20laws%20to%20end%20untouchability%20and%20kind%20of%20bring%20an%20end%20to%20caste%20discrimination.%20And%20finally%20in%201989%2C%20we%20had%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Atrocities%20Against%20SC%2FST%20Act%2C%20but%20in%20the%20book%2C%20you%20mentioned%20even%20after%20that%2C%20there%20have%20been%20so%20many%20instances%20of%20mass%20violence%20against%20the%20Dalits.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhether%20it%20was%20in%20the%201960s%20in%20Kilvenmani%20or%20Bathani%20Tola%2C%20atrocities%20have%20continued%20despite%20laws%2C%20specific%20laws%2C%20coming%20in%20to%20end%20injustice.%20This%20brings%20into%20question%20the%20whole%20legal%20struggle%20that%20has%20gone%20on%20for%20the%20past%20200%2C%20over%20200%20years.%20So%2C%20in%20your%20opinion%20where%20has%20Independent%20India%20gone%20wrong%20and%20where%20do%20we%20go%20from%20here%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGreat%20question.%20Because%20if%20you%20only%20look%20at%20what%20is%20there%20in%20the%20statute%20book%2C%20you%20won%E2%80%99t%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20where%20this%20deeply%20ingrained%20prejudice%20was%20coming%20from.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20legal%20history%20that%20preceded%20this%20enactment%2C%20you%20will%20then%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20why%20there%20is%20still%20so%20much%20impunity.%20The%20kind%20of%20violence%20that%20we%20saw%20post-independence%20was%20something%20that%20Gandhi%20in%20his%20lifetime%20did%20not%20see%20%E2%80%93%20violence%20targeting%20Dalits.%20Even%20Ambedkar%20did%20not%20see.%20Ambedkar%20passed%20away%20in%2056.%20And%20for%20that%20matter%2C%20even%20Nehru%20%E2%80%93%20who%20passed%20away%20in%2064%20%E2%80%93%20did%20not%20see.%20Because%20the%20first%20such%20instance%20of%20mass%20violence%20targeting%20Dalits%20took%20place%20in%20Kilvenmani%2C%20as%20you%20said%2C%20in%201968.%20And%20that%20set%20the%20template%20%E2%80%93%20not%20only%20for%20violence%2C%20for%20mass%20violence%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20an%20instance%20in%20which%20some%2042%20women%20and%20children%20belonging%20to%20the%20Dalit%20community%20were%20burnt%20alive%2C%20and%20they%20were%20all%20found%20in%20one%20room%2C%20all%20packed%20into%20one%20small%20room%20in%20a%20hut.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20was%20no%20proper%20investigation%2C%20no%20questions%20were%20answered%20by%20any%20of%20those%20judgments%20as%20to%20why%20so%20many%20of%20them%20were%20packed%20into%20one%20room%3B%20who%20forced%20them%20into%20that%20one%20room%3B%20why%20they%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20escape%3B%20who%20was%20stopping%20them%20from%20escaping.%20Nothing%2C%20none%20of%20that.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20what%20you%20see%20is%20that%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%20acquits%20all%20the%20ones%20who%20were%20convicted%20by%20the%20trial%20court%20and%20goes%20on%20to%20make%20some%20very%20classist%20statements%20that%20are%20hard%20to%20believe.%20This%20was%20the%20kind%20of%20sensitivity%20%E2%80%93%20or%20the%20lack%20of%20it%20%E2%80%93%20that%20India%20was%20displaying%20in%20the%2070s%2C%20that%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98it%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20believe%20that%20people%20who%20are%20so%20well%20off%2C%20who%20have%20owned%20cars%20would%20be%20party%20to%20such%20violence%2C%20or%20would%20be%20part%20of%20those%20mobs%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20tendency%2C%20this%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20mindset%20that%20India%20displayed%2C%20and%20that%20is%20what%20led%20to%20more%20and%20more%20such%20instances%20of%20violence%20%E2%80%93%20because%20of%20the%20template%20that%20Kilvenmani%20set%2C%20not%20only%20for%20violence%20but%20also%20for%20impunity%20%5Bbecause%20the%5D%20courts%2C%20the%20way%20they%20let%20off%20these%20killers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20led%20finally%20to%20the%20more%20stringent%20law%2C%20the%201989%20law%2C%20and%20that%20came%20during%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20last%20year%20in%20power.%20But%20it%20again%20showed%20that%20no%20matter%20how%20much%20you%20reform%20the%20law%2C%20how%20much%20you%20tighten%20the%20law%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20step%20forward%20for%20sure%20%E2%80%93%20but%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20enforcement%2C%20there%20are%20so%20many%20loopholes%20that%20people%20find%2C%20and%20ultimately%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20very%20little%20by%20way%20of%20justice.%20And%20to%20understand%20that%2C%20you%20need%20to%20go%20into%20this%20history.%20Because%20history%20shows%2C%20the%20legal%20history%20of%20these%20caste%20reforms%20shows%2C%20that%20many%20of%20these%20things%20that%20were%20done%20around%20the%20time%20of%20independence%20or%20post-independence%2C%20were%20all%20done%20out%20of%20sheer%20experience%20%E2%80%93%20there%20was%20no%20change%20of%20heart%2C%20there%20was%20no%20remorse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20that%20note%2C%20thank%20you%20so%20much%20for%20joining%20us.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20interesting%20point%20that%20you%20have%20ended%20with%2C%20that%20the%20battles%20for%20equality%20were%20not%20just%20between%20the%20upper%20caste%20and%20lower%20caste%20but%20it%20was%20also%20within%20the%20upper%20caste%2C%20within%20sections%20of%20progressives%2C%20sections%20of%20moderates%2C%20sections%20of%20certain%20people%20who%20were%20more%20radical%20than%20the%20others.%20For%20all%20this%20and%20more%2C%20please%20do%20read%20this%20book%20if%20you%20want%20to%20gain%20more%20insight%20into%20how%20legal%20reforms%20were%20conducted%20in%20India%20and%20how%20we%20have%20come%20to%20where%20we%20are%20today%2C%20and%20why%20the%20impunity%20against%20caste%20injustice%20continues%20until%20this%20day.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThank%20you%20so%20much%20for%20joining%20us%20at%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThank%20you%2C%20Sravasti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranscribed%20by%20Adi%20Roy.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693320349000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29200638%2FScreenshot-2023-08-29-at-8.05.51-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fmanoj-mitta-caste-based-violence-impunity-interview%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Discussing%20his%20latest%20book%20with%20Sravasti%20Dasgupta%2C%20Manoj%20Mitta%20says%20that%20whenever%20there%20is%20an%20instance%20of%20mass%20violence%2C%20one%20arm%20or%20another%20of%20the%20Indian%20state%20has%20betrayed%20caste%20prejudice.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fmanoj-mitta-caste-based-violence-impunity-interview%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Raksha%20Bandhan%20outfit%20inspiration%20from%20B-Town%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693319400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103179882%2Cimgsize-74038.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Falia-bhatt-sonam-kapoor-deepika-padukone-raksha-bandhan-outfit-inspiration-to-take-from-b-town-celebs%2Fphotostory%2F103179882.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103179882.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAlia%20Bhatt%2C%20Sonam%20Kapoor%2C%20Deepika%20Padukone%3A%20Raksha%20Bandhan%20outfit%20inspiration%20to%20take%20from%20B-town%20celebs%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Falia-bhatt-sonam-kapoor-deepika-padukone-raksha-bandhan-outfit-inspiration-to-take-from-b-town-celebs%2Fphotostory%2F103179882.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Article%20370%3A%20SC%20Asks%20Whether%20Its%20Reading%20Down%20Was%20Logical%20to%20Achieve%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Integration%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F08135608%2Fsupreme-court-file-pti.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EChief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20asked%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20August%2029%20whether%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20was%20a%20logical%20step%20to%20achieve%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20integration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20was%20hearing%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%2C%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Crecommendation%E2%80%9D%20used%20in%20the%20proviso%20to%20Article%20370%20(3)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20%E2%80%93%20before%20it%20was%20read%20down%20on%20August%205%2C%202019%20%E2%80%93%20came%20in%20for%20special%20scrutiny%20before%20the%20top%20court%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proviso%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1577416%2F%5C%22%3Esays%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Crecommendation%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20the%20State%20%E2%80%9Cshall%20be%20necessary%20before%20the%20president%20issues%20a%20notification%E2%80%9D%20declaring%20that%20this%20article%20%E2%80%9Cshall%20cease%20to%20be%20operative%20or%20shall%20be%20operative%20only%20with%20such%20exceptions%20and%20modifications%20and%20from%20such%20date%20as%20he%20may%20specify%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttorney%20General%20R.%20Venkataramani%20contended%20before%20the%20bench%20that%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Crecommendation%E2%80%9D%20should%20be%20construed%20as%20mere%20advice%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20it%20is%20not%20binding%20on%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20however%2C%20expressed%20his%20disagreement%20with%20such%20interpretation.%20According%20to%20him%2C%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Crecommendation%E2%80%9D%20in%20Article%20370(3)%20meant%20a%20positive%20decision%2C%20because%20the%20same%20Article%20also%20uses%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98consultation%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98concurrence%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98decision%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98advice%E2%80%99%20in%20different%20contexts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAG%20Venkataramani%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20could%20not%20have%20recommended%20to%20the%20president%20not%20to%20read%20down%20Article%20370%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20the%20question%20of%20the%20president%20overriding%20it%20did%20not%20arise.%20The%20Constituent%20Assembly%20could%20only%20recommend%20rendering%20Article%20370%20inoperative%2C%20he%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fday-2-of-article-370-case-constituent-assembly-is-distinguishable-from-partisan-parliament-sc-told%5C%22%3EDay%202%20of%20Article%20370%20Case%3A%20Constituent%20Assembly%20Is%20Distinguishable%20From%20Partisan%20Parliament%2C%20SC%20Told%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20president%20did%20not%20lose%20authority%20and%20power%20under%20Article%20370(3)%20just%20because%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20was%20no%20longer%20operative%2C%20having%20dissolved%20itself%20without%20such%20a%20recommendation.%20The%20power%20conferred%20on%20the%20president%20under%20Article%20370%20is%20a%20legislative%20power%2C%20not%20executive%2C%20he%20clarified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20observed%20that%20between%20absolute%20autonomy%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20in%201950%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%20integration%E2%80%9D%20on%20August%205%2C%202019%2C%20there%20was%20a%20chasm%20substantially%20bridged%20in%20between.%20He%20asked%20whether%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20was%20a%20logical%20step%20to%20achieve%20that%20integration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Solicitor-General%20(SG)%20Tushar%20Mehta%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Farticle-370-was-a-self-extinguishing-temporary-provision-centre-to-sc%2Farticleshow%2F103147089.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehad%20submitted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Article%20370(3)%20has%20an%20in-built%20extinguishing%20clause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20restoration%20of%20democracy%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20is%20important.%20He%20nudged%20the%20AG%20and%20the%20SG%20to%20take%20instructions%20from%20the%20%E2%80%9Chighest%20levels%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Croad%20map%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctime%20frame%E2%80%9D%20to%20restore%20democracy%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CProgression%20has%20to%20take%20place.%20It%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20a%20UT%20permanently%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20told%20the%20SG%2C%20who%20brought%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20statement%20in%20parliament%20that%20the%20government%20would%20confer%20statehood%20on%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20if%20the%20situation%20improved%2C%20and%20that%20it%20had%20no%20difficulty%20in%20doing%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELadakh%2C%20however%2C%20will%20remain%20a%20UT%2C%20the%20SG%20disclosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20taken%20instructions.%20The%20instructions%20are%20that%20Union%20territory%20is%20not%20a%20permanent%20feature.%20But%20I%20will%20make%20a%20positive%20statement%20the%20day%20after%20tomorrow.%20Ladakh%20will%20remain%20a%20Union%20territory%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mehta%20said%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20CJI%20had%20asked%20why%20the%20government%20could%20not%20declare%20a%20specific%20time%20frame%20for%20creating%20a%20Union%20territory%20to%20tackle%20national%20security%2C%20so%20that%20it%20could%20fulfil%20hopes%20that%20statehood%20would%20be%20restored%20soon.%20The%20bench%20quizzed%20the%20SG%20on%20the%20contours%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1659104%2F%5C%22%3EArticle%203%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20enables%20parliament%20to%20form%20new%20states%2C%20and%20alter%20areas%2C%20boundaries%20and%20names%20of%20existing%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20also%20sought%20to%20dissect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F589802%2F%5C%22%3EArticle%20370%20(1)%20(d)%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20makes%20the%20consultation%20with%20and%20concurrence%20of%20the%20state%20government%20mandatory%20for%20applying%20provisions%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20other%20than%20Articles%201%20and%20370.%20Consultation%20with%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20government%20was%20mandatory%20if%20the%20other%20provisions%20of%20the%20constitution%20related%20to%20matters%20specified%20in%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20(IoA)%2C%20while%20its%20concurrence%20was%20required%20for%20matters%20outside%20the%20IoA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fpublic-first-time-jammu-kashmirs-instrument-accession-india%5C%22%3EThe%20Backstory%20of%20Article%20370%3A%20A%20True%20Copy%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehta%20pointed%20out%20that%20there%20were%20several%20exercises%20of%20this%20provision%20during%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20and%20the%20concurrence%20of%20the%20governor%20was%20considered%20sufficient%20for%20the%20purpose.%20To%20a%20query%20from%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20on%20whether%20concurrence%20of%20the%20government%20meant%20that%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%2C%20Mehta%20suggested%20that%20its%20powers%20could%20be%20exercised%20by%20the%20governor%2C%20in%20its%20absence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20posed%20a%20specific%20question%20asking%20whether%20parliament%20can%20use%20Article%20367%20%E2%80%93%20dealing%20with%20interpretation%20%E2%80%93%20to%20amend%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amendment%20to%20Article%20367%20enabled%20parliament%20to%20read%20%E2%80%98Legislative%20Assembly%E2%80%99%20instead%20of%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20in%20order%20to%20circumvent%20the%20requirement%20of%20Article%20370%20(3)%2C%20which%20makes%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20mandatory%20for%20the%20president%20to%20make%20Article%20370%20inoperative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehta%20submitted%20that%20when%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20was%20dissolved%20without%20any%20recommendation%20to%20make%20Article%20370%20inoperative%2C%20the%20proviso%20to%20Article%20370(3)%20requiring%20such%20recommendation%20became%20otiose.%20The%20president%2C%20therefore%2C%20was%20left%20to%20his%20own%20choice%2C%20he%20suggested.%C2%A0%20He%20added%20that%20the%20removal%20of%20Article%20370%20%E2%80%93%20a%20transitory%20provision%20%E2%80%93%20furthers%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution%20and%20enhances%20equality%20and%20fraternity%2C%20the%20bedrock%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693319393000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F08135608%2Fsupreme-court-file-pti.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-hearing-sc-reading-down-article-370-logical-jammu-and-kashmir-integration%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20repeated%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20promise%20that%20statehood%20would%20be%20returned%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20but%20did%20not%20reveal%20any%20timeline%20yet.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-hearing-sc-reading-down-article-370-logical-jammu-and-kashmir-integration%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Asked%20About%20Her%20Reaction%20If%20She%20Caught