mg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F03164553%2Fimage-294.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2Fp%2Fgujarat-govt-on-thin-ice-for-selectively%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20people%E2%80%99s%20mandate%20for%20an%20elected%20representative%20to%20represent%20a%20constituency%20is%20badly%20devalued%20when%20she%2Fhe%20is%20advised%20by%20the%20powers%20that%20be%20not%20to%20speak%20on%20behalf%20of%20those%20constituents%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20legislature.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20right%20of%20an%20MP%20to%20represent%20his%20or%20her%20constituency%20in%20Parliament%20and%20the%20right%20of%20the%20electorate%20to%20be%20so%20represented%20in%20the%20apex%20legislature%20is%20considered%20sacrosanct.%20So%20when%20legislators%20are%20disqualified%20as%20MLAs%20or%20MPs%20after%20they%20are%20convicted%20and%20sentenced%20to%20two%20years%E2%80%99%20imprisonment%2C%20the%20judiciary%20has%20often%20stayed%20the%20conviction%20and%20the%20sentence%20so%20that%20their%20right%20to%20represent%20people%20and%20the%20right%20of%20the%20electorate%20to%20be%20represented%20in%20the%20legislature%20is%20restored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20example%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20staying%20the%20conviction%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20in%20a%20criminal%20defamation%20case%20is%20very%20instructive.%20The%20right%20of%20an%20MP%20to%20represent%20his%20constituency%20and%20the%20right%20of%20the%20electorate%20to%20be%20represented%20in%20Parliament%20should%20mean%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20to%20speak%20in%20Parliament%20regarding%20the%20problems%20of%20constituents%20and%20urge%20the%20government%20to%20find%20remedies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETwo%20Manipur%20MPs%20asked%20not%20to%20speak%20on%20no-confidence%20motion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20tragic%20that%20two%20MPs%20of%20Manipur%2C%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Naga%20People%E2%80%99s%20Front%2C%20supporting%20the%20Modi%20government%20at%20the%20Centre%2C%20were%20informally%20advised%20by%20the%20BJP%20leadership%20to%20refrain%20from%20speaking%20on%20the%20Manipur%20violence%20during%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20told%20that%20since%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20was%20speaking%20on%20the%20issue%20at%20length%2C%20they%20should%20keep%20away%20from%20the%20discussion.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20right%20to%20represent%20people%20and%20speak%20on%20their%20behalf%2C%20considered%20to%20be%20sacrosanct%2C%20could%20not%20be%20exercised%20by%20them%20when%20the%20parliamentary%20device%20of%20no-confidence%20motion%20was%20employed%20by%20the%20Opposition%20against%20the%20Modi%20Regime%20to%20ensure%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20that%20the%20PM%2C%20who%20had%20been%20silent%20on%20Manipur%2C%20should%20come%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20speak%20on%20violence%20and%20bloodshed%20in%20the%20State%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20305px)%2085vw%2C%20305px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29192656%2F343600733_782056540096419_6606661224714857866_n.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22305%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29192656%2F343600733_782056540096419_6606661224714857866_n.jpg%20968w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29192656%2F343600733_782056540096419_6606661224714857866_n-300x298.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29192656%2F343600733_782056540096419_6606661224714857866_n-150x150.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670526%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22304%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELorho%20S.%20Pfoze.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaga%20People%E2%80%99s%20Front%20MP%20Lorho%20S%20Pfoze%2C%20who%20supports%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA%20government%20at%20the%20Centre%2C%20told%C2%A0%3Ci%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fi%3E%20that%20BJP%20leaders%20advised%20him%20not%20to%20speak%20on%20the%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20during%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20no-confidence%20motion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPfoze%20represents%20the%20Outer%20Manipur%20constituency%2C%20which%20was%20badly%20hit%20by%20the%20violence.%20Speaking%20with%20Barkha%20Dutt%20and%20MojoStory%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DiAA4KC2SEJY%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20few%20BJP%20leaders%20had%20asked%20him%20not%20to%20speak.%20He%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20should%20have%20first%20asked%20me%20to%20speak%20even%20if%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20make%20a%20formal%20request.%20I%20wanted%20to%20speak%20on%20behalf%20of%20my%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeace%20in%20Manipur%20would%20be%20elusive%20if%20its%20MPs%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20speak%20in%20Parliament%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Dutt%20asked%20if%20he%20felt%20angry%20and%20dejected%20because%20as%20an%20MP%20from%20Manipur%20and%20ally%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20he%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20speak%20in%20the%20debate%20about%20his%20own%20people%2C%20he%20stated%20that%20the%20government%20should%20have%20asked%20him%20to%20speak%20because%20he%20is%20an%20alliance%20partner%20and%20represents%20Kukis%2C%20Meiteis%20and%20Nagas%20of%20his%20constituency%2C%20all%20victims%20of%20the%20havoc%20wrought%20on%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20asserted%20that%20the%20deprivation%20of%20that%20opportunity%20to%20express%20himself%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20behalf%20of%20his%20constituents%20made%20him%20dejected%2C%20sad%20and%20angry.%20However%2C%20out%20of%20respect%20for%20the%20government%2C%20he%20did%20not%20put%20forth%20his%20request%20to%20speak.%20He%20also%20asked%20if%20the%20plea%20of%20the%20government%20for%20peace%20to%20be%20restored%20would%20sound%20convincing%20if%20he%20is%20not%20allowed%20to%20speak%20and%20appeal%20for%20calm%20and%20peace%20in%20his%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20he%20told%C2%A0%3Ci%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0that%20his%20constituents%2C%20Kukis%2C%20Meiteis%20and%20Nagas%2C%20were%20very%20gravely%20impacted%20by%20the%20terrible%20violence.%20He%20was%20keen%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20discussion%20on%20the%20no-confidence%20motion.%20He%20would%20have%20flagged%20the%20point%20that%20the%20violence%2C%20largely%20targeting%20the%20Kuki-Zo%20community%2C%20should%20have%20been%20stopped.%20The%20nation%20could%20have%20appreciated%20the%20magnitude%20of%20the%20unprecedented%20problem%20they%20confronted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20added%20that%20because%20MPs%20of%20Manipur%20represent%20the%20people%20of%20the%20state%20in%20Parliament%2C%20they%20should%20have%20been%20asked%20to%20speak.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20would%20have%20built%20confidence%20in%20my%20people%20because%20elections%20are%20coming%20and%20it%20is%20needful%20for%20our%20people%20to%20know%20that%20the%20government%20is%20serious%20about%20dealing%20with%20the%20issues%20confronting%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPfoze%20also%20told%C2%A0%3Ci%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fi%3E%20that%20the%20only%20other%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20from%20Manipur%2C%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20R.K.%20Ranjan%20Singh%2C%20who%20is%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20External%20Affairs%2C%20was%20also%20informally%20advised%20not%20to%20speak%20during%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20no-trust%20motion.%20He%20did%20not%20request%20the%20Speaker%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20for%20permission%20to%20speak%20on%20the%20issue%20as%20he%20was%20sure%20that%20it%20would%20be%20rejected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EManipur%20MP%E2%80%99s%20questions%20on%20violence%20in%20the%20state%20were%20not%20picked%20up%20in%20Parliament%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20quite%20shocking%20to%20learn%2C%20from%20his%20interactions%20with%20Dutt%2C%20that%20fifty%20of%20his%20questions%20on%20Manipur%20were%20not%20picked%20up%20in%20any%20of%20the%20discussions%2C%20except%20one%20on%20education.%20It%20is%20a%20serious%20matter%20because%20the%20parliamentary%20device%20of%20asking%20questions%20is%20very%20critical.%20It%20holds%20the%20Government%20to%20account%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EManipur%20MP%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20expunged%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20when%20Mizoram%20MP%20K%20Vanlavena%20contradicted%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20statement%20that%20tribal%20people%20in%20Manipur%20came%20from%20Myanmar%2C%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chair%20Jagdeep%20Dhankar%20ordered%20it%20to%20be%20expunged.%20Vanlalvena%2C%20the%20only%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20from%20the%20Mizo%20National%20Front%2C%20is%20part%20of%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA%20and%20his%20remarks%20came%20in%20response%20to%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20observations%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDevaluation%20of%20Parliament%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20right%20of%20a%20Member%20to%20speak%20about%20his%2Fher%20constituents%20was%20violated%20when%20they%20were%20advised%20not%20to%20speak%20on%20the%20Manipur%20violence%2C%20which%20has%20been%20described%20in%20many%20circles%20as%20an%20ethnic%20conflict%20and%20a%20civil%20war.%20While%20moving%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%2C%20Saurabh%20Gogoi%20of%20the%20Congress%20had%20charged%20that%20even%20the%20BJP%20MPs%20representing%20Manipur%20were%20not%20allowed%20to%20speak%20on%20the%20sufferings%20inflicted%20on%20their%20constituents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EParliament%20must%20be%20used%20to%20erase%20communal%20distemper%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20India%20started%20functioning%20in%20December%201946%2C%20terrible%20communal%20violence%20and%20massive%20loss%20of%20life%20following%20Partition%20had%20raised%20serious%20concerns%20regarding%20its%20unity%20and%20integrity.%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20had%20famously%20stated%20that%20the%20Assembly%20would%20provide%20solutions%20to%20the%20communal%20distemper.%20It%20did%20this%20by%20framing%20a%20Constitution%20and%20providing%20a%20secular%20frame%20of%20governance%20and%20establishing%20a%20Republic%20neutral%20to%20all%20faiths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20when%20the%20country%20is%20witnessing%20a%20replay%20of%20pre-Partition%20communal%20discord%2C%20our%20MPs%20representing%20the%20mandate%20of%20their%20constituents%20must%20be%20allowed%20to%20speak%20for%20the%20restoration%20of%20peace%2C%20unity%20and%20sanity%2C%20so%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20India%20as%20a%20union%20of%20states%20is%20defended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDepriving%20the%20right%20of%20an%20MP%20to%20speak%20amounts%20to%20devaluation%20of%20Parliament%20itself.%20We%20need%20to%20arrest%20the%20trend%20so%20that%20the%20Parliament%20can%20provide%20solutions%20to%20the%20communal%20distemper%20which%20is%20badly%20tarnishing%20the%20image%20of%20India%20and%20endangering%20our%20unity%20and%20integrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3ES.N.%20Sahu%20served%20as%20Officer%20on%20Special%20Duty%20to%20President%20of%20India%20K.R.%20Narayanan.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693318200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F03164553%2Fimage-294.png%22%2C%22originID