0Kamach%20and%20Habalwar%20hamlets%20which%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20electricity%20yet%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kumari%2C%20mother%20of%20two%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20proposal%20has%20been%20approved%20and%20the%20work%20is%20expected%20to%20start%20very%20soon%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChatroo%20is%20the%20last%20tehsil%20in%20the%20high%20mountains%20that%20separate%20Kishtwar%20district%20in%20Jammu%20division%20from%20Anantnag%20in%20Kashmir.%20Chenab%20River%20gathers%20strength%20while%20passing%20through%20Kishtwar%2C%20starting%20from%20Chatroo%20and%2C%20according%20to%20one%20assessment%2C%20the%20river%20can%20produce%20up%20to%208000%20MW%20of%20clean%20electricity%20in%20Kishtwar%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29165435%2FIMG_5075-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29165435%2FIMG_5075-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29165435%2FIMG_5075-1-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29165435%2FIMG_5075-1-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670480%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKamach%20village%20lacks%20access%20to%20taped%20drinking%20water%20and%20residents%20are%20dependent%20on%20a%20water%20stream%20flowing%20down%20the%20hill%20to%20meet%20their%20daily%20needs.%20Photo%3A%20Jehangir%20Ali.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScattered%20on%20the%20steep%20slopes%20of%20a%20mountain%20which%20has%20a%20thick%20vegetative%20cover%20of%20pine%20trees%20and%20modest%20farms%20which%20sustain%20its%20villagers%2C%20Kamach%20can%20be%20reached%20from%20Watsar%20village%20through%20a%20moderately%20difficult%2C%20four-km%20trail%20that%20passes%20through%20a%20dense%20forest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20forest%20is%20home%20to%20the%20Himalayan%20brown%20bear%20and%20leopards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELack%20of%20basic%20amenities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hamlet%20also%20lacks%20any%20healthcare%20facility.%20In%20case%20of%20a%20medical%20emergency%2C%20the%20nearest%20help%20is%20an%20Ayush%20Wellness%20Centre%20where%20traditional%20medicine%20is%20used%20to%20treat%20patients.%20The%20centre%20is%20located%20in%20Thana%20village%20of%20Chingam%2C%20some%2014%20km%20away%2C%20half%20of%20which%20has%20to%20be%20covered%20on%20foot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20hospital%20is%20located%20some%2030%20kilometres%20away%20in%20Chatroo%20but%20finding%20transport%20to%20reach%20there%20is%20a%20herculean%20task.%20Although%20the%20villagers%20here%20have%20voter%20cards%2C%20they%20are%20too%20few%20to%20make%20any%20impact%20on%20the%20electoral%20battles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhenever%20there%20is%20a%20medical%20emergency%2C%20local%20men%20haul%20the%20patient%20on%20a%20cot%20and%20shoulder%20it%20down%20to%20the%20road.%20Thankfully%2C%20there%20have%20been%20no%20tragedies%20so%20far%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Asa%20Ram%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Kamach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29170259%2FIMG_5024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29170259%2FIMG_5024.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29170259%2FIMG_5024-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29170259%2FIMG_5024-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670487%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAsa%20Ram%2C%20a%20poor%20farmer%20of%20Kamach%2C%20makes%20a%20living%20by%20working%20as%20a%20labourer%20and%20he%20also%20grows%20vegetables%20and%20corn%20at%20a%20small%20farm.%20Jehangir%20Ali.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20educational%20institutions%20in%20the%20hamlet%20either.%20A%20few%20village%20kids%20use%20a%20steep%20mountain%20trail%20to%20reach%20a%20primary%20school%2C%20which%20is%20some%20five%20km%20away%20from%20Kamash%20in%20Zewal%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20electricity%2C%20the%20villagers%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20television%20sets%20or%20heating%20appliances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20today%E2%80%99s%20world%2C%20everything%20is%20dependent%20on%20electricity%2C%20but%20we%20are%20not%20among%20the%20fortunate%20ones%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shamo%20Nath%2C%2045%2C%20a%20farmer%20whose%20two%20children%20are%20enrolled%20at%20the%20school%20in%20Zewal.%20He%20said%20that%20his%20hamlet%20also%20lacked%20mobile%20phone%20connectivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29170016%2FIMG_4979.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29170016%2FIMG_4979.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29170016%2FIMG_4979-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29170016%2FIMG_4979-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670486%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EShamo%20Nath%20with%20his%20family%20at%20Kamach%20village%20of%20Kishtwar.%20Photo%3A%20Jehangir%20Ali.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20make%20a%20phone%20call%2C%20we%20have%20to%20go%20to%20another%20village%20two%20kilometres%20away%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImran%20Shah%2C%20a%20local%20journalist%2C%20said%20that%20there%20are%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20habitations%20in%20remote%20areas%20of%20Kishtwar%20such%20as%20Bonzwa%2C%20Kithar%2C%20Goruv%2C%20Keeri%20and%20Jeedo%20among%20others%20which%20are%20without%20electricity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20power%20projects%20in%20Kishtwar%20light%20up%20homes%20in%20the%20northern%20states%20of%20the%20country%20but%20our%20own%20villages%20have%20been%20denied%20their%20benefit%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shah%2C%20who%20freelances%20with%20local%20and%20national%20media%20outlets%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunil%20Kumar%20(25)%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Kamach%20who%20works%20as%20a%20delivery%20boy%20with%20a%20multinational%20online%20retailer%20in%20Jammu%20city%2C%20said%20that%20he%20visits%20his%20village%20once%20or%20twice%20in%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20get%20bored%20here%20easily%20because%20there%20is%20practically%20nothing%20to%20do.%20There%20are%20no%20shops%2C%20no%20roads%20and%20no%20mobile%20phone%20connectivity.%20I%20just%20want%20to%20run%20away%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kumar%2C%20who%20was%20returning%20home%20for%20a%20break%20and%20guided%20this%20reporter%20to%20the%20village%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshok%20Raina%20(28)%2C%20who%20works%20with%20a%20private%20firm%20in%20Punjab%2C%20said%20that%20the%20villagers%20depend%20on%20the%20generosity%20of%20people%20in%20the%20adjoining%20Chingam%20village%20to%20keep%20their%20mobile%20phones%20charged.%20The%20torches%20of%20mobile%20phones%20serve%20as%20searchlights%20at%20the%20time%20of%20emergency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20someone%20from%20the%20village%20goes%20to%20Chingam%2C%20you%20would%20see%20him%20returning%20with%20a%20pile%20of%20power%20banks.%20As%20it%20is%20cloudy%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20solar%20power%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20work.%20Many%20people%20burn%20wood%20to%20light%20up%20their%20homes%20at%20night%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESub-Divisional%20Magistrate%2C%20Chatroo%2C%20Showkat%20Hayat%20Mattoo%2C%20said%20that%20there%20are%20some%20hamlets%20in%20Chingam%20tehsil%20of%20Kishtwar%20which%20have%20not%20been%20connected%20with%20the%20power%20grid%20due%20to%20difficult%20topography.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20remote%20and%20difficult-to-reach%20area.%20For%20one%20hamlet%2C%20a%20solar%20power%20project%20is%20in%20the%20pipeline%20while%20two%20last%20hamlets%20in%20the%20tehsil%20are%20going%20to%20be%20connected%20to%20the%20electricity%20grid%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeputy%20Commissioner%20Kishtwar%20Dr.%20Devansh%20Yadav%20claimed%20that%20Kamach%20is%20a%20seasonal%20habitation%20where%20solar%20lights%20have%20been%20provided%20to%20the%20residence%20by%20the%20district%20administration.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20residents%20of%20Kamach%20migrate%20from%20Khawra%20village%20during%20summers%20which%20is%20some%201.5%20km%20away%2C%20hence%20it%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20categorised%20as%20a%20village%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Yadav%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Mohan%20Lal%2C%2050%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Kamach%2C%20said%20that%20the%20villagers%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20small-time%20farmers%20or%20raise%20livestock%20for%20a%20living%2C%20spend%20most%20time%20of%20the%20year%20in%20the%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20live%20here%20for%20eight%20to%20nine%20months%20in%20a%20year.%20Does%20it%20mean%20that%20it%20is%20a%20%E2%80%98seasonal%20habitation%E2%80%99%3F%20During%20winters%2C%20we%20are%20forced%20to%20leave%20because%20there%20is%20no%20road%20or%20electricity%2C%E2%80%9D%20Lal%2C%20a%20farmer%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Yadav%2C%20the%20Deputy%20Commissioner%2C%20said%20that%20the%20local%20Panchayat%20has%20proposed%20grid%20connectivity%20to%20the%20houses%20in%20Kamach%20this%20financial%20year%2C%20%E2%80%9CRs%204%20lakh%20budget%20has%20been%20proposed%20by%20the%20Panchayat%20for%20providing%20electricity%20to%20the%20remaining%20villagers%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20district%20administration%20official%20said%20that%20a%20proposal%20to%20procure%2018%20poles%20has%20been%20floated.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20some%2010-12%20hamlets%2C%20including%20in%20the%20remote%20areas%20of%20Padder%20which%20are%20without%20electricity.%20However%2C%20all%20these%20villages%20will%20be%20electrified%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693313696000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29165734%2FIMG_4998.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fjk-projects-in-kishtwar-light-up-homes-in-other-states-but-not-this-hamlet-in-the-region%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20some%20200%20inhabitants%20of%20Kamach%20village%2C%20electricity%2C%20roads%2C%20hospital%2C%20and%20other%20basic%20amenities%20are%20still%20a%20pipedream.%20Villagers%20have%20to%20cover%2014%20kms%20on%20foot%20to%20get%20to%20the%20nearest%20health%20facility.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fjk-projects-in-kishtwar-light-up-homes-in-other-states-but-not-this-hamlet-in-the-region%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ameesha%20had%20a%20bit%20of%20'attitude'%3A%20Anil%20Sharma%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693313326000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103178491%2Cimgsize-250994.cms%22%2C%22originID%2