h%20this%20experimentation%2C%20it%20was%20established%20that%20the%20technology%20accelerated%20growth%20and%20yielded%20higher%20produce%20compared%20to%20prevalent%20pot-based%20systems%20like%20the%20bato%20bucket%20(inspired%20by%20Dutch%20technology)%20and%20grow%20bag-based%20systems%20(non-recirculation%20type%2C%20inspired%20by%20Israeli%20technology)%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20soilless%20cultivation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20method%20is%20not%20labour%20intensive%20like%20traditional%20farming%20as%20it%20is%20fully%20automatic.%20We%20have%20timers%20that%20are%20set%20in%20advance%20that%20provide%20and%20sprinkle%20required%20nutrients%20according%20to%20the%20plant%E2%80%99s%20requirements.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMaking%20it%20accessible%20for%20local%20farmers%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20a%20few%20arguments%20that%20Dr%20Sethi%20presented%20on%20the%20need%20for%20such%20a%20technology%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20most%20important%20reason%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20barren%20land%20in%20India%20that%20can%20be%20used%20for%20this%20purpose.%20Besides%2C%20this%20technology%20allows%20farmers%20and%20gardeners%20to%20grow%20food%20anywhere%20%E2%80%94%20from%20a%20closed%20room%20to%20a%20small%20terrace%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20will%20also%20generate%20employment%20in%20the%20country.%20Right%20from%20a%20homemaker%20with%20a%20spare%20room%20in%20her%20house%20to%20an%20unemployed%20youth%2C%20anyone%20can%20easily%20use%20the%20technology%20to%20grow%20plants%20with%20a%20little%20training.%20They%20can%20consume%20it%20and%20sell%20the%20excess%20in%20the%20market%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20reason%20why%20Dr%20Sethi%20thinks%20the%20technology%20is%20important%20is%20that%20it%20saves%20water.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20recirculation%20mode%2C%20with%20the%20use%20of%20HHT%2C%20we%20can%20save%20about%2060%20to%2090%25%20water%20depending%20on%20the%20plant%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20making%20it%20accessible%20to%20the%20local%20farmers%2C%20he%20says%20that%20there%20are%20plans%20underway.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FPAU-4-1692279060.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Using%20HHT%2C%20the%20university%20has%20grown%20vegetables%20like%20tomatoes%2C%20cherry%20tomatoes%2C%20cucumber%2C%20bell%20pepper%20and%20capsicum%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FPAU-4-1692279060.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FPAU-4-1692279060-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FPAU-4-1692279060-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FPAU-4-1692279060-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FPAU-4-1692279060-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-327505%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EUsing%20HHT%2C%20the%20university%20has%20grown%20vegetables%20like%20tomatoes%2C%20cherry%20tomatoes%2C%20cucumber%2C%20bell%20pepper%20and%20capsicum.%20Picture%20credit%3A%20V%20K%20Sethi%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20many%20industries%20of%20hydroponics%20in%20India%2C%20but%20most%20of%20them%20import%20it%20from%20either%20Israel%20or%20China.%20This%20increases%20the%20cost.%20What%20we%20have%20created%20saves%20the%20cost%20by%20three%20times.%20If%20the%20cost%20is%20less%2C%20the%20technology%20automatically%20becomes%20more%20accessible.%20We%20are%20also%20in%20the%20process%20of%20making%20a%20manual%20for%20farmers%20and%20other%20users%2C%20and%20are%20also%20open%20to%20selling%20its%20commercial%20rights%20to%20the%20industry%20to%20make%20it%20more%20accessible%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20travelled%20across%20the%20world%20and%20have%20seen%20farmers%20using%20different%20innovative%20technologies%20to%20grow%20food.%20But%20this%20technology%20of%20merging%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F255453%2Fkota-startup-hydroponics-eeki-foods-iit-bombay-organic-high-quality-tomatoes-cucumbers-eggplant-bitter-gourd-soli-free-india-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubstrate%20and%20water-based%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20not%20available%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world.%20I%20feel%20very%20proud%20that%20I%20was%20able%20to%20develop%20it%20and%20we%20call%20it%20%3Cem%3Eswadeshi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(made%20in%20India).%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20a%20country%20of%20small%20land%20holdings%20and%20the%20technology%20is%20especially%20designed%20to%20accommodate%20small-scale%20farmers.%20Our%20motto%20is%20to%20focus%20on%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Esabka%20vikas%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(development%20for%20all)%20and%20this%20technology%20does%20the%20same.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E)%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692280952000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FPAU-1-1692278262.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D327451%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Developed%20by%20Dr%20V%20P%20Sethi%2C%20head%20of%20the%20department%20of%20mechanical%20engineering%20at%20Punjab%20Agricultural%20University%2C%20the%20Hybrid%20Hydroponics%20Technology%20combines%20both%20two%20types%20hydroponics%20systems%20to%20significantly%20reduce%20water%20wastage